Authors, necessary corrections in the text have been made in the &quot;track changes&quot; mode and important notes have been added. Authors should take care to make the indicated corrections carefully. After the revisions are made, the article should be read carefully from beginning to end. The revised version will become acceptable.','Cemal Turan','Dear Editor, the necessary corrections have been made to the article. I believe that the article can be considered acceptable after the authors make the corrections carefully.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1110851-81_2.docx','15-08-2024',3,4,4,0,1),(82,111,2923,'2024-08-06',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Cemal Turan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(83,110,2961,'2024-08-06','2024-08-06',2,'',1,0,'The study compared well-known translation tools. It is suitable to be published in the journal. Some additions and corrections are required. The title is suitable. The content is sufficient. No information about the data set is provided. The comparison with the literature is considered insufficient.','Yakup Kutlu','.','NULL','NULL','06-08-2024',4,4,4,0,0),(84,110,2979,'2024-08-06',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(85,114,2980,'2024-08-07','2024-08-08',2,'',1,0,'Necesarry corrections are indicated in the text','Cemal Turan','Necesarry corrections are indicated in the text','../reviewreports/TES-1147841-85.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1147841-85_2.docx','08-08-2024',4,4,4,1,1),(86,112,2923,'2024-08-07',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Servet Dogdu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,1),(87,112,2928,'2024-08-07',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Servet Dogdu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(88,111,2980,'2024-08-08','2024-08-12',2,'',1,0,'Dear Authors,\r\nNecessary corrections are given in the text. Authors should make corrections carefully.The paper can be accepted after corrections.','Cemal Turan','Dear Editor, \r\nNecessary corrections are given in the text. Authors must make corrections carefully. The paper can be accepted after corrections.','../reviewreports/TES-1110851-88.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1110851-88_2.docx','12-08-2024',3,3,3,0,1),(89,116,2923,'2024-08-09',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(90,116,2948,'2024-08-09','2024-08-17',2,'',1,0,'Authors can find minor corrections within the text.','Ali Uyan','The article is suitable for publication.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1162599-90_2.docx','17-08-2024',5,5,5,0,1),(91,116,2984,'2024-08-09',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(92,117,2924,'2024-08-12','2024-08-14',2,'',1,0,'Dear Authors,\r\n\r\nThe necessary corrections are indicated in the manuscript. It would be appropriate to revise the manuscript in line with the specified corrections.\r\n\r\nBest regards','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\n\r\nThe necessary corrections have been indicated in the manuscript. It would be appropriate for the authors to revise the manuscript according to these corrections.\r\n\r\nBest regards','../reviewreports/TES-1174455-92.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1174455-92_2.docx','14-08-2024',4,4,4,0,1),(93,117,2948,'2024-08-12','2024-08-20',2,'',1,0,'Dear authors,\r\nThe necessary minor corrections have been made in the text in &quot;track changes&quot; mode. It would be beneficial for the authors to read these changes again from beginning to end after accepting them.','Ali Uyan','The article can be accepted for publication after minor corrections are made by the authors.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1174455-93_2.docx','20-08-2024',5,5,5,0,1),(94,117,2987,'2024-08-12',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Servet Dogdu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(95,116,2981,'2024-08-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(96,116,2989,'2024-08-13',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(97,116,2990,'2024-08-13','2024-08-14',2,'',1,0,'Değerli hocam, bu önemli kayıt için teşekkürler. Ufak düzeltme önerileri metin içinde yer almaktadır.','Ali Uyan','Değerli Hocam, yazarlarımıza öneriler, MS metni içinde yer almaktadır. İyi çalışmalar diliyorum. Mümkün ise, bir Orjinal Araştırma Makalesi olarak basılmasını önerebilirim. Saygılarımla.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1162599-97_2.docx','14-08-2024',4,4,5,0,1),(98,95,1,'2024-08-16',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,1),(100,120,2948,'2024-08-28','2024-08-28',1,'',1,0,'Your article has been accepted for publication.','Ali Uyan','The article is suitable for publication in its current version.','NULL','NULL','28-08-2024',5,5,5,1,1),(101,126,2986,'2024-09-02',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Servet Dogdu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(102,126,2948,'2024-09-02','2024-09-14',2,'',1,0,'In this study, the authors performed genetic and morphological analysis of Belone belone populations distributed along the Bulgarian and Turkish coasts of the Black Sea. The article is suitable for publication. However, several changes and corrections have been made to the main text. The authors can read the article from beginning to end and submit the final version after accepting the edits I made in the &quot;Track Changes&quot; mode.','Servet Dogdu','The article is suitable for publication.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1267834-102_2.docx','14-09-2024',5,5,5,0,0),(103,127,3009,'2024-09-10',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(104,127,3010,'2024-09-10',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(105,127,2981,'2024-09-10',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(106,127,2990,'2024-09-19',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(107,127,2989,'2024-09-19','2024-09-25',2,'',1,0,'you can find all my recommendations on MS','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor\r\nthe MS acceptable after minor revisions\r\nregards','../reviewreports/TES-1273544-107.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1273544-107_2.docx','25-09-2024',4,5,5,0,1),(108,128,3012,'2024-09-25',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(109,128,3013,'2024-09-25',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(110,128,3014,'2024-09-25',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(111,127,2948,'2024-09-25','2024-09-25',2,'',1,0,'The necessary edits have been made in the text. It is useful for the authors to check the article again after accepting these edits. The final version will be acceptable for publication.','Ali Uyan','The article is suitable for publication.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1273544-111_2.docx','25-09-2024',3,3,4,0,1),(112,129,2924,'2024-10-02',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(113,129,17,'2024-10-02',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(114,129,2948,'2024-10-02',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Servet Dogdu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(115,128,2989,'2024-10-02',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(116,128,3015,'2024-10-02',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(117,128,3016,'2024-10-03',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(118,128,3017,'2024-10-03','2024-10-24',0,'',1,0,'Dear Editor,\r\nI have completed the review of the submitted manuscript, and I have come to the conclusion that it should be rejected for publication. The reasons for this decision are outlined below:\r\n1.	Lack of Scientific Contribution: Although it is stated that new species records are given for the Region, there is no detailed information about the species. This situation shows that the article does not add sufficient information to the literature in the relevant field.\r\n2.	Methodological Weaknesses: The methods employed in the study are insufficient to adequately address the research objectives. Specifically, the data collection process has not been thoroughly explained, which raises concerns about the reliability and reproducibility of the results.\r\n3.	Theoretical Gaps: The manuscript shows inconsistencies with the existing theoretical framework in the field. The arguments presented are not well-supported by relevant literature, and the theoretical foundation is weak. Previous studies in the region have not been detailed enough. This indicates a lack of depth and alignment with the scientific context.\r\n4.	Interpretation of Results: I think one of the biggest problems is in this section. The discussion of the results is shallow and does not engage with the literature in a meaningful way. The authors fail to provide sufficient interpretation of the significance and implications of the findings, leaving their contribution unclear to the reader.\r\n5.	Writing and Presentation Issues: There are numerous grammatical and typographical errors throughout the manuscript, which affect the overall readability and clarity of the text. Furthermore, the figures and tables are not presented in a coherent manner and lack sufficient explanation, detracting from the comprehensibility of the work.\r\nIn light of the above shortcomings, I believe the manuscript in its current form is not suitable for publication. \r\nSincerely,\r\nDr. Neslihan TÜRKÇÜ\r\n','Ali Uyan','Dear Author(s),\r\nI have completed the review of your manuscript and would like to provide you with my feedback. At this stage, I do not recommend the publication of your work in its current form, but I believe that by addressing the following points, you can significantly improve it for future submission. All corrections are indicated as comments on the attached word file.\r\n1.	Lack of Scientific Contribution: Although the manuscript finds new recorded species in the subject and region examined, it seems to be insufficient in conveying detailed information.\r\n2.	Methodological Weaknesses: The methods you have used do not seem sufficient to meet the objectives of the study. Specifically, the data collection process has not been adequately explained, which raises concerns about the reliability and reproducibility of your results. Additionally, the statistical analyses are not conducted properly, which undermines the validity of your findings.\r\n3.	Theoretical Gaps: The arguments presented are not sufficiently supported by the relevant literature, and the manuscript appears to lack a solid theoretical foundation. Strengthening your theoretical framework and aligning it more closely with the existing literature could significantly improve the scientific merit of your work.\r\n4.	Interpretation of Results: The discussion of your results could benefit from a deeper analysis and a stronger connection to the literature. Providing clearer explanations about the meaning and significance of your findings, as well as how they contribute to the field, would enhance the value of your manuscript.\r\n5.	Writing and Presentation Issues: There are several grammatical and typographical errors throughout the manuscript, which negatively impact its readability. Additionally, the figures and tables are not adequately explained and are not presented in a coherent manner with the text. There is a general lack of information and harmony in the manuscript. Each section needs to be expanded in an informative way. The graphical abstract is missing. Journal Writing Rules should be carefully reviewed and re-prepared. Reference Writing Rules should be carefully reviewed and re-prepared.Improving these elements would help make your manuscript easier to understand and more accessible to readers.\r\nI believe there is potential to strengthen your manuscript by addressing these weaknesses. If you are able to revise and improve upon these areas, your work will be on a much stronger footing.\r\nBest regards,\r\nReviewer\r\n','../reviewreports/TES-1281398-118.doc','NULL','24-10-2024',1,4,3,0,0),(119,128,2948,'2024-10-11','2024-10-12',4,'',1,1,'Authors can find all edits in Reviewed MS File. I strongly recommend that all necessary edits made in &quot;Track the Changes&quot; mode be accepted and the issues I have mentioned in my notes be carefully considered. After all edits are complete, the article can be accepted for publication.','Ali Uyan','After major revisions have been made, the article may be accepted for publication.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1281398-119_2.doc','12-10-2024',3,4,4,0,1),(120,130,3021,'2024-10-16','2024-10-22',1,'',1,0,'Well written article.','Ali Uyan','Well written article.','../reviewreports/TES-1305385-120.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1305385-120_2.docx','22-10-2024',5,4,5,0,1),(121,130,3022,'2024-10-16',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(122,130,3020,'2024-10-16','2024-10-16',2,'',1,0,'Dear authors:\r\nYour manuscript is very good, it requires only these minor changes:\r\n1- Complement with other recent references.\r\n2- In authors contribution you mentioned experiments (??)\r\n3- I suggest include in citations to WORMS (www.marinespecies.org), it is a very good, updated and complete web site.\r\nMany success and blessings !!!\r\n','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor:\r\nThe manuscript is very good, it requires only minor changes previous to its publication.\r\nThank you for your consideration','NULL','NULL','16-10-2024',5,4,4,0,1),(123,130,3023,'2024-10-17',NULL,-1,'',0,0,NULL,'Cemal Turan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(124,130,2952,'2024-10-19',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(125,130,3025,'2024-10-19',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(126,130,2948,'2024-10-28','2024-10-29',4,'',1,0,'Dear authors,\r\n\r\nYour revised article has been subjected to a second review process because numerous major errors were detected and have been brought into compliance with the journal&#39;s guide. You can find the notes in the text and follow the edits made carefully in the &quot;Track Changes&quot; mode and accept them. After accepting all edits, carefully read the final version from beginning to end and submit it.','Ali Uyan','The article may be accepted after major revisions have been made.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1305385-R1-126_2.docx','29-10-2024',3,4,4,0,1),(127,131,3027,'2024-11-02',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(128,131,3026,'2024-11-02','2024-11-06',2,'',1,0,'Dear authors,\r\n\r\nFirst of all, thank you for your work. Upon reviewing your article, I believe it would be improved with some specific corrections in English writing and a few additions. I have noted the revisions I would like in the attached file.  Best regards.','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\n\r\nOnce the suggested corrections are made, the article will be ready for publication.\r\n\r\nBest regards','../reviewreports/TES-1318098-128.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1318098-128_2.docx','06-11-2024',4,4,3,0,1),(129,131,2918,'2024-11-02','2024-11-05',1,'',1,0,'-','Ali Uyan','-','../reviewreports/TES-1318098-129.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1318098-129_2.docx','05-11-2024',5,4,5,0,1),(130,131,11,'2024-11-02',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(131,128,2948,'2024-11-06','2024-11-06',2,'',1,0,'Dear authors,\r\n\r\nYour article has undergone a second revision process. The Reviewed MS file contains all the corrections I strongly recommended. Please carefully consider my suggestions and revise your article for the final version.','Ali Uyan','The article can be accepted if the authors make all necessary edits.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1281398-R1-131_2.doc','06-11-2024',3,4,4,0,1),(132,132,3030,'2024-11-07',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(133,132,3009,'2024-11-07',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(134,132,3031,'2024-11-07',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(135,132,3032,'2024-11-11',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(136,132,3033,'2024-11-11','2024-11-14',1,'',1,0,'The topic is good, you just need to check the language.','Ali Uyan','The topic is good, you just need to check the language.','../reviewreports/TES-1326778-136.docx','NULL','14-11-2024',4,4,4,0,1),(137,132,3034,'2024-11-11','2024-11-11',1,'',1,0,'Dear Author,\r\nConsidering the subject, its integrity and results, the study presents new, original and important data. The manuscript is acceptable for publication.','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\nConsidering the subject, its integrity and results, the study presents new, original and important data. The manuscript is acceptable for publication.','NULL','NULL','11-11-2024',5,4,5,0,1),(138,132,3035,'2024-11-13',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(139,132,3036,'2024-11-13',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(140,132,3037,'2024-11-13',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(141,132,2948,'2024-11-25',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Servet Dogdu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(142,132,12,'2024-11-25','2024-11-25',2,'',1,0,' It can be accepted after minor revisions','Servet Dogdu',' It can be accepted after minor revisions','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1326778-142_2.docx','25-11-2024',4,4,4,0,1),(143,133,2948,'2025-01-12','2025-01-15',2,'',1,0,'Authors can check and accept the edits I added in &quot;track changes&quot; mode. The article can be accepted for publication after these edits.','Ali Uyan','The article has been accepted for publication after minor corrections.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1338957-143_2.docx','15-01-2025',5,5,5,0,1),(144,133,2923,'2025-01-12','2025-01-17',2,'',1,0,'The MS accepted after minor revisions.','Ali Uyan','The MS accepted after minor revisions.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1338957-144_2.docx','17-01-2025',5,4,5,0,1),(145,133,3040,'2025-01-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(146,134,3030,'2025-02-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(147,134,3009,'2025-02-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(148,134,3031,'2025-02-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(149,135,2948,'2025-02-18',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(150,135,3045,'2025-02-20',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(151,134,3046,'2025-02-24',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(152,134,3033,'2025-02-24',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(153,134,3034,'2025-02-24','2025-02-24',2,'',1,0,'Dear Author\r\nThis paper is acceptable.It is recommended to correct a few word errors.\r\n','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor \r\nThis paper is acceptable.It is recommended to correct a few word errors.\r\n','../reviewreports/TES-1349247-153.docx','NULL','24-02-2025',4,4,5,1,1),(154,134,3035,'2025-02-24',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(155,134,2948,'2025-02-24','2025-02-28',2,'',1,0,'Authors can find all major grammatical corrections and added notes in the revised manuscript file. Once all of these have been done, the manuscript can be accepted for publication.','Ali Uyan','The article can be accepted for publication after the major edits have been made.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1349247-155_2.docx','28-02-2025',4,5,4,1,1),(156,135,3048,'2025-02-24',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(157,135,3047,'2025-02-24','2025-02-26',4,'',1,0,'The review is attached. Best wishes','Ali Uyan','The review is attached. Best wishes','../reviewreports/TES-1359759-157.docx','NULL','26-02-2025',3,2,4,1,1),(158,135,3049,'2025-02-24',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(159,135,3050,'2025-02-24','2025-02-25',4,'',1,0,'Dear Editor and Authors, The manuscript needs better English, and I have also made a few corrections in the manuscript. After these improvements, the manuscript can be accepted. Kind regards,','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor and Authors, The manuscript needs better English, and I have also made a few corrections in the manuscript. After these improvements, the manuscript can be accepted. Kind regards,','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1359759-159_2.docx','25-02-2025',3,4,4,1,1),(160,135,3051,'2025-02-24',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(161,135,3052,'2025-02-24',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(162,137,3058,'2025-03-10',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(163,137,3059,'2025-03-10','2025-03-22',2,'',1,0,'The writing style is acceptable but requires a few improvements, particularly in the title. The attached corrected manuscript includes all these improvements (such as the title).','Ali Uyan','New country-specific records of Lessepsian migrant species are highly important as they demonstrate the rate of spread of these species toward the western Mediterranean Sea.','../reviewreports/TES-1373246-163.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1373246-163_2.docx','22-03-2025',4,4,5,1,0),(164,137,3060,'2025-03-10',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(165,136,3058,'2025-03-10','2025-03-25',4,'',1,0,'The authors report on “Occurrence of Wahoo, Acantocybium solandri in Libya, first record from the north African coast”. This is interesting research which fill a gap in the distribution and occurrence of species in Libyan water. However, some marks and comments are provided below.\r\nTitle:\r\nTitle should be changed, and consequently the documented locations of records of Acantocybium solandri in the Mediterranean; because recent study has documented the species\r\nhttps://ejabf.journals.ekb.eg/article_407425_5f00b3f635642c91668fb9c69c12e2f9.pdf \r\nAbstract\r\nLocation of catch, morphometric and meristic measurements should be mentioned accurately.\r\nIntroduction\r\nNeeds comprehensive literature around the study\r\nMaterials and Methods\r\n-	Scale (for example ruler) should be used to indicate the true length of the photographed fish.\r\n-	Morphometric and meristic measurements, along with identification keys, all should be provided.\r\nResults \r\nPhotographs and video of both fish captures off the coasts of Talamitha region, Libya. There is no videos!, the site name should be mentioned on the map.\r\nThe pectoral fins are relatively short and positioned close to the head. This sentence is repeated!\r\nDiscussion\r\nShould de updated, because recent study has documented the species\r\nhttps://ejabf.journals.ekb.eg/article_407425_5f00b3f635642c91668fb9c69c12e2f9.pdf \r\nalso, discussion should imply the potential reasons for the observation of the specie in Libyan waters.\r\n','Servet Dogdu','Dear editor, thank you \r\nThe authors report on “Occurrence of Wahoo, Acantocybium solandri in Libya, first record from the north African coast”. This is interesting research which fill a gap in the distribution and occurrence of species in Libyan water. However, some marks and comments are provided below.\r\nTitle:\r\nTitle should be changed, and consequently the documented locations of records of Acantocybium solandri in the Mediterranean; because recent study has documented the species\r\nhttps://ejabf.journals.ekb.eg/article_407425_5f00b3f635642c91668fb9c69c12e2f9.pdf \r\nAbstract\r\nLocation of catch, morphometric and meristic measurements should be mentioned accurately.\r\nIntroduction\r\nNeeds comprehensive literature around the study\r\nMaterials and Methods\r\n-	Scale (for example ruler) should be used to indicate the true length of the photographed fish.\r\n-	Morphometric and meristic measurements, along with identification keys, all should be provided.\r\nResults \r\nPhotographs and video of both fish captures off the coasts of Talamitha region, Libya. There is no videos!, the site name should be mentioned on the map.\r\nThe pectoral fins are relatively short and positioned close to the head. This sentence is repeated!\r\nDiscussion\r\nShould de updated, because recent study has documented the species\r\nhttps://ejabf.journals.ekb.eg/article_407425_5f00b3f635642c91668fb9c69c12e2f9.pdf \r\nalso, discussion should imply the potential reasons for the observation of the specie in Libyan waters.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n','../reviewreports/TES-1361323-165.docx','NULL','25-03-2025',5,5,5,0,1),(166,136,3059,'2025-03-10','2025-03-22',2,'',1,0,'The writing style is acceptable but requires a few improvements, particularly in the title. The attached corrected manuscript includes all these improvements (such as the title).','Servet Dogdu','New country-specific records of Lessepsian migrant species are highly important as they demonstrate the rate of spread of these species toward the western Mediterranean Sea.','../reviewreports/TES-1361323-166.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1361323-166_2.docx','22-03-2025',4,4,5,0,1),(167,136,3060,'2025-03-10',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Servet Dogdu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(168,136,2948,'2025-03-14',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(169,136,2986,'2025-03-14',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(170,136,3062,'2025-03-14',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(171,137,1,'2025-03-14',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(172,138,2990,'2025-03-22',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(173,138,17,'2025-03-22',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(174,138,2984,'2025-03-22',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(175,138,16,'2025-03-26','2025-04-18',2,'',1,0,'Suitable for Publication with Minor Correction\r\nThe article is scientifically meaningful and the observation is valuable for its rarity. However, some adjustments are needed in terms of language, structure and presentation.','Ali Uyan','Suitable for Publication with Minor Correction\r\nThe article is scientifically meaningful and the observation is valuable for its rarity. However, some adjustments are needed in terms of language, structure and presentation.','../reviewreports/TES-1386843-175.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1386843-175_2.docx','18-04-2025',4,3,4,0,1),(176,139,3030,'2025-04-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(177,139,3009,'2025-04-18','2025-04-18',4,'',1,0,'The manuscript presents a regionally valuable record, but in its current form, it lacks scientific depth, methodological transparency, and analytical clarity. With careful restructuring, reduction of overstatements, and integration of objective environmental context, the manuscript could reach publication standards.\r\n\r\nAlthough single-individual records are acceptable in first documentation studies, the authors go far beyond the limitations of their dataset, making generalizations that are not supported by any environmental, ecological, or comparative data. A more cautious, concise, and methodologically transparent revision is required.\r\n\r\nMajor Issues\r\n1. Overinterpretation and Speculative Claims\r\nThe authors derive wide-reaching conclusions about species expansion, habitat suitability, and ecological preferences based on a single specimen. Phrases such as &quot;potential for permanent population&quot;, &quot;expanding distribution&quot;, and &quot;critical insights into ecological requirements&quot; are scientifically unwarranted in this context.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: All such speculative statements must be removed or reframed as hypotheses for future research. The authors must clearly state that their conclusions are limited by the absence of environmental data and replicates.\r\n\r\n2. Methodological Insufficiency\r\nThe methods section is vague and lacks critical information:\r\n\r\nNo GPS coordinates of the sampling site.\r\n\r\nNo information on whether the habitat types (mud, sand, artificial) were actively surveyed.\r\n\r\nNo description of sampling effort, replicates, depth, or temporal scope.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: The authors must clarify whether this finding resulted from a systematic survey or an incidental observation. If other habitats were surveyed, a brief protocol should be included.\r\n\r\n3. Lack of Environmental Context\r\nDespite making claims about “biotope preference”, the authors provide no environmental parameters (e.g., temperature, salinity, light intensity, algal composition, wave exposure, etc.) to support the classification or preference.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: At minimum, a descriptive profile of the habitat (depth, slope, substrate granulometry, algal dominance) should be added. If no measurements were made, this should be acknowledged as a limitation.\r\n\r\n4. Figures Missing or Incomplete\r\nFigures referred to in the text (Figures 1 and 2) were not available for review. Moreover, it is unclear whether the images contain clear diagnostic features supporting the identification.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: High-resolution images of the specimen (with scale bars) and a properly labeled map (with coordinates and scale) must be included.\r\n\r\n5. Inflated and Redundant Language\r\nThe manuscript contains many repetitive and exaggerated expressions that are stylistically inappropriate for scientific writing. This weakens the manuscript’s clarity and objectivity.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: Simplify the language. Avoid using phrases such as “structural integrity of habitats” or “critical insight into conservation” unless backed by data.\r\n\r\n6. Reference Management Issues\r\nGuerao & Abelló (1999) is cited twice in the introduction.\r\n\r\nSome references are used in a list-like fashion without integration or critical comparison.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: Eliminate duplicate references and improve integration of literature—especially comparing P. marmoratus biotopes from previous studies.\r\n\r\nMinor Issues\r\nThe abstract should refer to this as a “first record” rather than “first observation”.\r\n\r\nThe “Data Availability Statement” is too generic. Specimen metadata (date, catalog number, coordinates, depth) should be included in a table or supplementary file.\r\n\r\nLine-by-line grammar and style improvements are recommended during revision.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\nThis manuscript provides a potentially useful record of a decapod species in a new region of the Eastern Mediterranean. However, it currently reads more like a field report than a peer-reviewed scientific article. The authors must:\r\n\r\nScale back their interpretations,\r\n\r\nImprove methodological transparency,\r\n\r\nAdd missing data and figures,\r\n\r\nStrengthen the scientific tone.\r\n\r\nWith major revision, this manuscript could serve as a valid contribution to regional biodiversity literature.','Ali Uyan','The manuscript presents a regionally valuable record, but in its current form, it lacks scientific depth, methodological transparency, and analytical clarity. With careful restructuring, reduction of overstatements, and integration of objective environmental context, the manuscript could reach publication standards.\r\n\r\nAlthough single-individual records are acceptable in first documentation studies, the authors go far beyond the limitations of their dataset, making generalizations that are not supported by any environmental, ecological, or comparative data. A more cautious, concise, and methodologically transparent revision is required.\r\n\r\nMajor Issues\r\n1. Overinterpretation and Speculative Claims\r\nThe authors derive wide-reaching conclusions about species expansion, habitat suitability, and ecological preferences based on a single specimen. Phrases such as &quot;potential for permanent population&quot;, &quot;expanding distribution&quot;, and &quot;critical insights into ecological requirements&quot; are scientifically unwarranted in this context.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: All such speculative statements must be removed or reframed as hypotheses for future research. The authors must clearly state that their conclusions are limited by the absence of environmental data and replicates.\r\n\r\n2. Methodological Insufficiency\r\nThe methods section is vague and lacks critical information:\r\n\r\nNo GPS coordinates of the sampling site.\r\n\r\nNo information on whether the habitat types (mud, sand, artificial) were actively surveyed.\r\n\r\nNo description of sampling effort, replicates, depth, or temporal scope.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: The authors must clarify whether this finding resulted from a systematic survey or an incidental observation. If other habitats were surveyed, a brief protocol should be included.\r\n\r\n3. Lack of Environmental Context\r\nDespite making claims about “biotope preference”, the authors provide no environmental parameters (e.g., temperature, salinity, light intensity, algal composition, wave exposure, etc.) to support the classification or preference.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: At minimum, a descriptive profile of the habitat (depth, slope, substrate granulometry, algal dominance) should be added. If no measurements were made, this should be acknowledged as a limitation.\r\n\r\n4. Figures Missing or Incomplete\r\nFigures referred to in the text (Figures 1 and 2) were not available for review. Moreover, it is unclear whether the images contain clear diagnostic features supporting the identification.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: High-resolution images of the specimen (with scale bars) and a properly labeled map (with coordinates and scale) must be included.\r\n\r\n5. Inflated and Redundant Language\r\nThe manuscript contains many repetitive and exaggerated expressions that are stylistically inappropriate for scientific writing. This weakens the manuscript’s clarity and objectivity.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: Simplify the language. Avoid using phrases such as “structural integrity of habitats” or “critical insight into conservation” unless backed by data.\r\n\r\n6. Reference Management Issues\r\nGuerao & Abelló (1999) is cited twice in the introduction.\r\n\r\nSome references are used in a list-like fashion without integration or critical comparison.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: Eliminate duplicate references and improve integration of literature—especially comparing P. marmoratus biotopes from previous studies.\r\n\r\nMinor Issues\r\nThe abstract should refer to this as a “first record” rather than “first observation”.\r\n\r\nThe “Data Availability Statement” is too generic. Specimen metadata (date, catalog number, coordinates, depth) should be included in a table or supplementary file.\r\n\r\nLine-by-line grammar and style improvements are recommended during revision.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\nThis manuscript provides a potentially useful record of a decapod species in a new region of the Eastern Mediterranean. However, it currently reads more like a field report than a peer-reviewed scientific article. The authors must:\r\n\r\nScale back their interpretations,\r\n\r\nImprove methodological transparency,\r\n\r\nAdd missing data and figures,\r\n\r\nStrengthen the scientific tone.\r\n\r\nWith major revision, this manuscript could serve as a valid contribution to regional biodiversity literature.','NULL','NULL','18-04-2025',3,5,5,1,1),(178,139,2981,'2025-04-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(179,137,3027,'2025-04-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(180,137,2948,'2025-04-18',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(181,140,3066,'2025-05-14','2025-05-15',2,'',1,0,'Please suggest that can we predict the weather by this model','Ali Uyan','quality for the paper is good and founds to be original work. accepted after minor revisions','../reviewreports/TES-1400301-181.docx','NULL','15-05-2025',4,5,5,1,1),(182,140,3067,'2025-05-14',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(183,140,3068,'2025-05-14',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(184,142,17,'2025-05-29',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(185,142,2981,'2025-05-29',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(186,142,2980,'2025-05-29','2025-06-10',2,'',1,0,'Dear Authors\r\n\r\nNecessary corrections are indicated in red colour in the text. Authors should take note of the suggested corrections.\r\n\r\nBest wishes\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\n\r\nNecessary corrections are indicated in the body text. After minor corrections, the manuscript can be accepted by me.\r\n\r\nBest regards\r\n','../reviewreports/TES-1420628-186.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1420628-186_2.docx','10-06-2025',3,4,3,0,1),(187,143,3009,'2025-06-05',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(188,143,2980,'2025-06-05','2025-06-10',2,'',1,0,'Dear Authors\r\n\r\nNecessary minor corrections are indicated in the body text. There are some word errors in the study. Also, there is no cite to Figure 1 and Table 1 and Table 5,6 and Table 7 in the text. All References need to be reviewed according to the journal rules. It is recommended that you check the paper again after changes have been made.\r\n\r\nBest wishes','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\n\r\nThe study titled Spatial and Temporal Changes in Macrozoobenthic Communities in Mezitli Streams Mountain is an important study conducted in this region.\r\n\r\nThere are some word errors in the study. Also, there is no cite to Figure 1 and Table 1 and Table 5,6 and Table 7 in the text. All References need to be reviewed according to the journal rules.\r\n\r\nThe suggested corrections must be made carefully by the authors. The manuscript can be accepted by me after the corrections.\r\n\r\nBest regards','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1435698-188_2.docx','10-06-2025',3,4,4,0,1),(189,143,3010,'2025-06-05',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(190,144,3009,'2025-06-25',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(191,144,3010,'2025-06-25',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(192,144,3090,'2025-06-25','2025-07-02',0,'',1,0,'Dear Author(s),\r\nIt is an ideal study, especially for the opportunistic feeding habits of the green turtle. Green turtles are known to be omnivorous as sub-adults and herbivorous as adults. You claim that adults exhibit opportunistic feeding behavior and feed on fish, etc. While the general framework actually represents a useful finding, it remains unclear how you determined the adult stage, and there is no clear methodology. This casts serious doubt on the findings. How you estimated the carapace lengths of individuals observed in seawater remains unclear. \r\nI am attaching my humble suggestions on the manuscript; I hope they will be useful.','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\nIt is an ideal study, especially for the opportunistic feeding habits of the green turtle. Green turtles are known to be omnivores as subadults and herbivores as adults. The authors claim that adults exhibit opportunistic feeding behavior and feed on fish, etc. While the general framework actually represents a beneficial finding, it remains unclear how the authors determine the stage of adult, and they do not propose a clear methodology. This casts serious doubt on the findings. It is not clear how the carapace lengths of individuals observed in seawater were estimated. Mean carapace lengths for sub-adult and adult individuals in green turtles for the Mediterranean population are already available. The lack of clarity on how adult individuals were identified is an important shortcoming, and the manuscript is therefore in need of serious revision.\r\nA careful examination of Figure 3 in the manuscript shows that the turtles in the image are sub-adult individuals. It would be clearer if the authors shared images of individuals they consider adults. Otherwise, it is already known that sub-adults are omnivores.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1443224-192_2.docx','02-07-2025',1,2,2,0,1),(193,144,3083,'2025-07-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(194,144,2948,'2025-07-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(195,144,2986,'2025-07-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(196,144,1,'2025-07-12',NULL,-1,'',0,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(197,144,2997,'2025-07-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(198,144,3,'2025-07-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(199,144,3090,'2025-07-12','2025-07-22',4,'',1,0,'Dear Author,\r\nMS has been re-presented in the current version with very few changes and similar to the previous version. My humble suggestion is to re-present the MS taking into account my suggestions from the previous version. Also, it would be helpful to clearly state the methodology used to estimate the shell size (ImageJ, Biomorph, etc.). Either make this methodology explicit or remove the estimates of carapace size from the MS.','Yakup Kutlu','Dear Editor,\r\nThe authors have made very few changes to the current version and re-presented it as similar to the previous version. I humbly suggest that they take into account my suggestions in the previous version and re-present MS. Also, it would be useful if they clearly state the methodology (such as ImageJ) used to estimate the size of the carapace. The authors should either state this method clearly or remove their estimates of the size of the carapace from the MS.','NULL','NULL','22-07-2025',2,3,3,0,1),(200,144,1,'2025-07-12',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(201,145,2987,'2025-07-30','2025-08-06',4,'',1,0,'Please take into account of my correction notes, of which I typed in red throuhout the manuscript.','Ali Uyan','The manuscript is worth to publish in the Tethys journal after the corrections.','../reviewreports/TES-1451856-201.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1451856-201_2.docx','06-08-2025',3,3,4,0,1),(202,145,3097,'2025-07-30',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(203,145,3098,'2025-07-30',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(204,145,2987,'2025-07-30',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(205,145,2990,'2025-08-06',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(206,145,2976,'2025-08-06',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(207,145,3024,'2025-08-06',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(208,145,3025,'2025-08-06',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(209,145,2972,'2025-08-06','2025-08-20',2,'',1,0,'I do not consider this article to provide highly specific information, given that a record was reported off Bodrum two years ago and the two locations are very close to each other. My personal recommendation is that the content should be enriched, at least with detailed information on the biology of the mentioned species, and that the grammar of the article should be improved. I also recommend that the requested change of article’s title be taken into consideration.','Ali Uyan','The review of the article entitled Additional Record of Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (Apogonidae) from the Aegean Sea (Gökova Bay, Türkiye) has been completed and the file has been uploaded. The article is suitable for publication with minor revisions. I recommend that the requested change of the article’s title be taken into consideration.','../reviewreports/TES-1451856-209.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1451856-209_2.docx','20-08-2025',3,2,2,0,1),(210,146,16,'2025-08-23','2025-09-04',2,'',1,0,'This manuscript reports the first visual documentation of Caesio cf. teres in the Mediterranean Sea, observed off the coast of Yayladağ, Türkiye. The study is timely and relevant in the context of marine bioinvasions and Lessepsian migration, offering valuable photographic evidence to support the observation.\r\n\r\nStrengths:\r\n\r\nWell-structured and clearly written.\r\n\r\nThorough morphological comparison with closely related species.\r\n\r\nProvides useful geospatial and environmental context for the sighting.\r\n\r\nMinor Revisions Required:\r\n\r\nLanguage editing: Minor grammatical and typographic issues throughout (e.g., “was visual” should be “was visually observed”; “videoed” → “recorded on video”).\r\n\r\nFigure 1 needs better resolution and clearer labeling.\r\n\r\nReference formatting: Ensure all references follow a consistent citation style.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: Accept with minor revisions','Ali Uyan','This manuscript reports the first visual documentation of Caesio cf. teres in the Mediterranean Sea, observed off the coast of Yayladağ, Türkiye. The study is timely and relevant in the context of marine bioinvasions and Lessepsian migration, offering valuable photographic evidence to support the observation.\r\n\r\nStrengths:\r\n\r\nWell-structured and clearly written.\r\n\r\nThorough morphological comparison with closely related species.\r\n\r\nProvides useful geospatial and environmental context for the sighting.\r\n\r\nMinor Revisions Required:\r\n\r\nLanguage editing: Minor grammatical and typographic issues throughout (e.g., “was visual” should be “was visually observed”; “videoed” → “recorded on video”).\r\n\r\nFigure 1 needs better resolution and clearer labeling.\r\n\r\nReference formatting: Ensure all references follow a consistent citation style.\r\n\r\nRecommendation: Accept with minor revisions','NULL','NULL','04-09-2025',4,4,4,0,1),(211,146,2981,'2025-08-23',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(212,146,2984,'2025-08-23',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(213,146,2980,'2025-08-23',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(214,146,3084,'2025-08-30',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(215,146,17,'2025-08-30',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,0,0),(216,146,2948,'2025-09-05','2025-09-05',2,'',1,0,'The article&#39;s quality, innovation, originality, and contribution to the field are all good. The first record of the species, thought to have been introduced via the Suez Canal, on the northeastern Mediterranean coast, has resulted in the addition of a new species to Türkiye&#39;s non-indigenous fish inventory. The species&#39; potential future distribution and potential biotic interactions with native species should be closely monitored. The file to which I applied minor revisions has been uploaded to the system. After these, the article will be suitable for publication.','Ali Uyan','Dear editors, the article can be published after minor editing.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1466439-216_2.docx','05-09-2025',5,5,5,0,1),(217,149,3009,'2025-09-11',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(218,149,3107,'2025-09-11',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(219,149,3048,'2025-09-11',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(220,149,3083,'2025-09-11',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(221,149,3015,'2025-09-11',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(222,149,2972,'2025-09-11','2025-10-01',4,'',1,0,'I believe the study&#39;s methodological limitations (low number of units, lack of a control area) need to be addressed. Clarifying these would make the article more balanced and credible.\r\n\r\nThe English is generally understandable, but fluency and coherence need improvement. Some sentences are long and could be simplified for clarity.','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor, I have completed my review. I hope my comments will be helpful for the authors.','../reviewreports/TES-1492253-222.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1492253-222_2.docx','01-10-2025',3,3,3,1,0),(223,150,17,'2025-09-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(224,150,2980,'2025-09-18','2025-09-25',4,'',1,0,'Dear Authors,\r\nAlthough the study is scientifically significant, the paper requires major revisions to improve it. The lionfish is represented as a single species in the Mediterranean. The presence of P. volitans in the Mediterranean has not been confirmed. Authors should correct the species name to P. miles in the manuscript to avoid confusion. Necessary corrections are indicated in the main text.\r\nSuggested Corrections;\r\nThe title should be revised to &quot;Assessing the Bioecology of the Invasive Lionfish (Pterois miles) in the Eastern Mediterranean Sea.\r\nAbstract and Keywords should be revised.\r\nIntroduction section: In the introduction section, some sentences or words should be edited.\r\nMaterial and Methods:  A better map should be provided and should be in black and white for Figure 1.\r\nAge estimation: The scale picture showing the maximum age rings should be given as a separate figure.\r\nResults and Discussion: The Result and Discussion sections need to be written better.\r\nSome words and punctuation marks indicated in the notes should be corrected.\r\nFood Composition: Individuals and values of stomach contents should be given in detail according to family and genus.\r\nThe legends in Tables and Figures should be corrected to P. miles.\r\nLength-weight and growth value studies conducted with lionfish in previous years should be presented separately in tables according to chronological year order.\r\nFigure 9. For the X axis;  Hunting date should be presented as months (eg; Sept. 2020; Oct. 2020 etc)\r\nThe manuscript appears to lack numerous references cited or discussed in detail for the Mediterranean Sea. Missing references are listed below. Authors should review and discuss these sources in the manuscript.\r\nKaragyaurova T., Koulocheri Z., Theocharis A., Mavrouleas D., Kalaentzis K., Kondylatos G., Klaoudatos D. (2024) Population structure of the Devil firefish Pterois miles (Bennett, 1828) in Rhodes, Greece. Conference Paper. June 2024. \r\n https://www.researchgate.net/publication/382049437 \r\n\r\nDemirci B., Demirhan. SA (2022) Food Composition and Dietary Overlap of the Lionfish Species in Iskenderun Bay. NESciences, 2022, 7(3): 228-239 doi: 10.28978/nesciences.1163001 \r\nYılmaz, S. Demirhan, S.A (2020) Age, growth parameters and food composition of Invasive Red Lionfish (Pterois volitans L., 1758) in İskenderun Bay. NESciences, 2020, 5(2): 82-91 \r\nDağhan, H. & Demirhan, S. A. (2020). Some bio-ecological characteristics of lionfish Pterois miles (Bennett, 1828) in Iskende¬run Bay. Marine and Life Sciences, 2(1): 28-40.\r\n\r\nSome references should be again checked according to the journal rules.\r\nBest wishes\r\n\r\n','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\nAlthough the study is scientifically important, the paper needs major corrections to be better. Necessary corrections are given in the text as a docx version. After substantial major corrections, the paper can be accepted by me.\r\nBest regards\r\n','../reviewreports/TES-1500240-224.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1500240-224_2.docx','25-09-2025',2,3,3,1,0),(225,150,3010,'2025-09-18',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(226,148,2963,'2025-09-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(227,147,2963,'2025-09-18',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Yakup Kutlu',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(228,147,1,'2025-09-23','2025-09-23',1,'',1,0,'\r\nThe manuscript titled Developing E-Pharmacy Platform for Disabled and Elderly Individuals presents the design and implementation of a web-based e-pharmacy platform aimed at improving medication accessibility for elderly and disabled individuals. The study addresses an important societal problem and offers a technically solid and socially impactful solution. The work is original in its approach, combining social responsibility with a secure, scalable digital infrastructure. The inclusion of user testing and feedback enhances the practical contribution of the study.  Therefore it could be accepted to publish','Yakup Kutlu','\r\nThe manuscript titled Developing E-Pharmacy Platform for Disabled and Elderly Individuals presents the design and implementation of a web-based e-pharmacy platform aimed at improving medication accessibility for elderly and disabled individuals. The study addresses an important societal problem and offers a technically solid and socially impactful solution. The work is original in its approach, combining social responsibility with a secure, scalable digital infrastructure. The inclusion of user testing and feedback enhances the practical contribution of the study. this manuscript makes a valuable contribution to the field of digital health technologies and social responsibility projects. Therefore it could be accepted to publish','NULL','NULL','23-09-2025',4,3,3,1,1),(229,147,2970,'2025-09-23','2025-09-23',1,'',1,0,'The manuscript presents a well-structured and innovative digital health solution that effectively addresses the medication accessibility challenges of elderly and disabled individuals. The methodology is sound, the findings are clearly supported, and therefore, the article is suitable for acceptance.','Yakup Kutlu','The manuscript presents a well-structured and innovative digital health solution that effectively addresses the medication accessibility challenges of elderly and disabled individuals. The methodology is sound, the findings are clearly supported, and therefore, the article is suitable for acceptance.','NULL','NULL','23-09-2025',3,3,3,1,1),(230,148,2970,'2025-09-23','2025-09-23',0,'',1,0,'The manuscript titled “Artificial Intelligence in Dental Imaging for Disease Detection and Treatment” presents a comprehensive literature review on the application of AI in dental diagnostics. The paper is well-structured, clearly written, and covers a broad spectrum of AI models, datasets, and outcomes. The inclusion of comparative results from different studies adds significant value, and the discussion highlights both the strengths and limitations of current approaches.  Given the scientific merit, relevance, and clarity of this paper, I recommend acceptance of the manuscript.','Yakup Kutlu','The manuscript titled “Artificial Intelligence in Dental Imaging for Disease Detection and Treatment” presents a comprehensive literature review on the application of AI in dental diagnostics. The paper is well-structured, clearly written, and covers a broad spectrum of AI models, datasets, and outcomes. The inclusion of comparative results from different studies adds significant value, and the discussion highlights both the strengths and limitations of current approaches.  Given the scientific merit, relevance, and clarity of this paper, I recommend acceptance of the manuscript.','NULL','NULL','23-09-2025',4,4,4,1,0),(231,148,2961,'2025-09-23','2025-09-23',1,'',1,0,'The manuscript provides a clear and comprehensive review of artificial intelligence applications in dental imaging, highlighting both current achievements and future research opportunities. Its relevance, structure, and contribution to the field make it suitable for publication. the manuscript be accepted for publication.','Yakup Kutlu','The manuscript provides a clear and comprehensive review of artificial intelligence applications in dental imaging, highlighting both current achievements and future research opportunities. Its relevance, structure, and contribution to the field make it suitable for publication. the manuscript be accepted for publication.','NULL','NULL','23-09-2025',4,4,4,1,0),(232,151,3010,'2025-09-25',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(233,151,2980,'2025-09-25','2025-10-02',4,'',1,0,'Dear Authors,\r\n\r\nAlthough the present manuscript fills a gap in this field, some deficiencies need to be addressed for the manuscript to become a research article. Minor corrections are indicated in the text, and also, necessary suggestions are presented below.\r\nSuggestions;\r\nThe survey questions used in the study should be documented as supplementary documentation. The analysis methods used in the study are not clearly stated. Furthermore, no tables or graphical presentations are provided for the results\r\n.\r\nBest wishes\r\n','Ali Uyan','Dear Editor,\r\n\r\nAlthough the study is scientifically important, the paper needs major corrections to be better. Necessary corrections are given in the text and reviewer comments as a docx version by me. After substantial major corrections, the paper can be accepted.\r\n\r\nBest regards\r\n','../reviewreports/TES-1514276-233.docx','../reviewreports/TES-1514276-233_2.docx','02-10-2025',3,4,4,1,0),(234,151,3009,'2025-09-25',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(235,152,2948,'2025-09-25','2025-09-28',2,'',1,0,'In this study, the authors examined the genetic structure of Belone populations from the Aegean, Marmara, and Black Sea coasts using COI and 12S rRNA datasets. I have made the necessary edits in the text using &quot;track changes&quot; mode. Authors are welcome to read and accept these edits. After these minor revisions, the article will be suitable for publication.','Ali Uyan','Dear editors, the article is acceptable after minor revisions are completed.','NULL','../reviewreports/TES-1529487-235_2.docx','28-09-2025',5,5,5,0,1),(236,149,3119,'2025-10-06',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(237,149,3120,'2025-10-06',NULL,-1,'',0,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(238,149,3017,'2025-10-06',NULL,-1,'',1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0),(239,149,3025,'2025-10-06',NULL,-1,'',-1,0,NULL,'Ali Uyan',NULL,NULL,'','',0,0,0,1,0);
