ogorum, 104, 165-173.\r<br>Silpa, S., Srihari, M., Pavan-Kumar, A., Roul, S. K., Russell, B. C., Jaiswar, A. K. (2021). Mistaken by dots: Revealing the misidentification of Saurida lessepsianus (Actinopterygii: Aulopiformes: Synodontidae) along the west coast of India (eastern Arabian Sea). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 51(2), 185-191.\r<br>SriHari, M., Silpa, S., Pavan-Kumar, A., Bhushan, S., Nayak, B. B., Abidi, Z. J. (2021). Stock characterization of Greater Lizardfish, Saurida tumbil (Bloch, 1795) along the west coast of India using morphological and molecular markers. Marine Biology Research, 17(2), 107-119.\r<br>Tajima, F. (1989). Statistical method for testing the neutral mutation hypothesis by DNA\r<br>polymorphism. Genetics, 123(3), 585-595.\r<br>Tan, M. P., Sammogam, R., Nur, N. F. M., Yusoff, N. I. S. M., Jaafar, T. N. A. M., Nor, S. A. M., Sung, Y. Y., Danish‑Daniel, M., Megarajan, S. (2022). Genetic polymorphism and phylogenetic relationships of the brushtooth lizardfish (Saurida undosquamis)(Aulopiformes: Synodontidae) based on mitochondrial DNA markers. Marine Biodiversity, 52(1), 13.\r<br>Tikochinski, Y., Russell, B., Hyams, Y., Motro, U., Golani, D. (2016). Molecular analysis of the recently described lizardfish Saurida lessepsianus (Synodontidae) from the Red Sea and the Mediterranean, with remarks on its phylogeny and genetic bottleneck effect. Marine Biology Research, 12(4), 419-425.\r<br>Turan, C., Ozturk, B., Caliskan, M., Duzgunes, E., Gurlek, M., Yaglioglu, D., Hazar, D., Sevenler, S. (2009). Genetic variation of Atlantic horse mackerel (Trachurus trachurus) in the Turkish waters. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 50(3), 207-213.\r<br>Turan, C., Erguden, D., Gurlek, M., Cevik, C., Turan, F. (2015). Molecular systematic analysis of shad species (Alosa spp.) from Turkish marine waters using mtDNA genes, Turkish Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 15(1), 149-155.\r<br>Turan, C., Erguden, D., Gurlek, M. (2016). Climate change and biodiversity effects in Turkish seas. Natural and Engineering Sciences, 1, 15-24.\r<br>Turan, C., Gurlek, M., Basusta, N., Uyan, A., Dogdu, S. A., Karan, S. (2018). A checklist of the non-indigenous fishes in Turkish marine waters. Natural and Engineering Sciences, 3(3), 333-358.\r<br>Turan, C., Ivanova, P. P., Raykov, V. S., Gurlek, M., Erguden, D., Yaglioglu, D., Giragosov, V. (2019). Genetics structure analysis of turbot (Scophthalmus maximus, Linnaeus, 1758) in the Black and Mediterranean Seas for application of innovative Management Strategies. Frontiers in Marine Science, 6, 740, 1-9\r<br>Turan, C., Ergenler, A., Doğdu, S. A., Turan, F. (2021). Age and growth of Red Sea goatfish, Parupeneus forsskali from Iskenderun Bay, Northeastern Mediterranean Sea. Journal of Ichthyology, 61, 758-763.\r<br>Tureli, C., Erdem, U. (1997). The growth performance of red mullet (Mullus barbatus Linnaeus, 1758) and brushtooth lizardfish (Saurida undosquamis (Richardson, 1848)) from the coastal region of Adana Province (Iskenderun Bay, Turkey). Turkish Journal of Zoology, 21(3), 329-334.\r<br>Turker, D., Zengin, K., Bal, H. (2020). Length-weight relationships of 11 lessepsian immigrant fish species caught from Mediterranean coast of Turkey (Antalya Bay). Acta Aquatica Turcica, 16(2), 301-304.\r<br>Uyan, A., Turan, C., Gurlek, M., Yaglioglu, D. (2020). Genetic and bio-ecologic characteristics of common pandora Pagellus erythrinus from the eastern Mediterranean coast of Turkey for the ecosystem-based fishery management. Genetics of Aquatic Organisms, 4(1), 29-37.\r<br>Wotton, R. J. (1990). Ecology of teleost fishes. Fish and fisheries series 1. Chapman & Hall. UK. 404 pp.\r<br>Yaglioglu, D., Turan, C. (2012). Colonization and genetic changes of Indo-Pacific immigrant Saurida undosquamis (Richardson, 1848)(lizardfish) in the Mediterranean Sea. Journal of Black Sea/Mediterranean Environment, 18(3), 329-340.\r<br>Yang, T., Huang, X., Jiang, Y. (2022). Reveal the Population Genetic Characteristics of Bombay Duck (Harpadon nehereus) in Coastal Waters of China with Genotyping-by-Sequencing Technique. Journal of Ocean University of China, 21(5), 1373-1380.\r<br>Yedier, S., Kontas, S., Bostanci, D. (2020). Length-length and length-weight relationships of Lessepsian Saurida undosquamis from the İskenderun Bay (Eastern Mediterranean, Turkey). Journal of the Institute of Science and Technology, 10(1), 616-623.\r<br>Yemisken, E., Dalyan, C., Eryilmaz, L. (2014). Catch and Discard Fish Species of Trawl Fisheries in the Iskenderun Bay (North-eastern Mediterranean) with Emphasis on Lessepsian and Chondricthyan Species. Mediterranean Marine Science, 15, 380-389.',1,1,'1-16',1,2024,1,615,397,0,'10.5281/zenodo.10878150','10878150','{\"created\": \"2024-03-26T12:59:35.163032+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2024-03-26T12:59:35.314357+00:00\", \"id\": 10878150, \"conceptrecid\": \"10878149\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Genetic and Some Bio-Ecological Characteristics of Lessepsian Lizardfish Saurida lessepsianus from the Northeastern Mediterranean Sea\", \"publication_date\": \"2024-03-26\", \"description\": \"Genetic structure and some bio-ecological characteristics of lessepsian lizardfish Saurida lessepsianus populations collected from the Iskenderun, Mersin, and Antalya Bays were revealed by mtDNA sequencing of Cyt b dataset and length-weight relationships and the parameters of von Bertalanffy growth function. The highest genetic divergence was detected between the Mersin and Antalya populations (0.0026), whereas the lowest was between the Iskenderun and Antalya populations (0.0014). The length-weight relationships for all individuals of Iskenderun, Mersin, and Antalya populations were calculated as W = 0.0042 x L3.2207, W = 0.0039 x L3.1627 and W = 0.0196 x L2.6515, respectively. The von Bertalanffy growth parameters (L\\u221e, k, and to) were estimated for all individuals as L\\u221e = 47.33 cm, k = 0.024, and to = -1.28 for Iskenderun; L\\u221e = 41.74 cm, k = 0.085 and to = -1.72 for Mersin and L\\u221e = 50.99 cm, k = 0.154 and to = -2.41 for Antalya. This study examines the genetic structure and bio-ecological characteristics of the S. lessepsianus populations on the Mediterranean coast of T\\u00fcrkiye together for the first time. Genetic findings and bio-ecological parameters of populations generally support each other and can provide support for future studies.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Ali Uyan\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Cemal Turan*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Servet Ahmet Do\\u011fdu\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Mevl\\u00fct G\\u00fcrlek\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Deniz Ya\\u011fl\\u0131o\\u011flu\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Bekta\\u015f S\\u00f6nmez\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Saurida lessepsianus\", \"population genetics\", \"mtDNA sequencing\", \"growth parameters\", \"Northeastern Mediterranean\"], \"license\": \"cc-by-4.0\", \"journal_title\": \"Tethys Environmental Sciences\", \"journal_volume\": \"1\", \"journal_issue\": \"1\", \"journal_pages\": \"1-16\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Zenodo\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.10878150\", \"recid\": 10878150}}, \"title\": \"Genetic and Some Bio-Ecological Characteristics of Lessepsian Lizardfish Saurida lessepsianus from the Northeastern Mediterranean Sea\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/10878150\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/3e27630f-ded3-425c-b6ff-d7dbce9641cd\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/10878150\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/10878150/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 10878150, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(72,'Servet Dogdu','dogduservet@gmail.com','','',0,0,'dogduservet@gmail.com','Deneme_22 Nisan_2024','',0,'Parrotfish are an important group in the coral reef ecosystem that maintain ecological stability and have a close relationship with coral reefs. Around the world, parrotfish and coral reefs are being destroyed due to human activities and global climate change. Here, we investigated the\r\ndiversity of parrotfish in the South China Sea (SCS) using DNA barcoding, and initially established a DNA barcode database of the SCS parrotfish. A total of 1620 parrotfish specimens, belonging to 23 species of 6 genera in the family Scaridae, were collected in the SCS, accounting for 64% of the\r\nparrotfish species in the SCS. Genetic distance analysis at each taxonomic level showed that the average genetic distance was 0.23% within species, 8.52% within genus and 13.89% within family. The average inter-specific distance was 37.04-fold the intra-specific distance. Barcode gap analysis\r\nshowed that 6 of the 21 parrotfish species with multiple samples had no barcode gap, resulting in an overall identification success rate of 74%. The ABGD analysis revealed that there could be 37 potential operational taxonomic units (OTUs) and the BIN analysis showed 32 identifiable taxonomic units, which by far exceed the number of morphologically previously known species. Overall, this study complements the lack of parrotfish DNA barcode sequences, and our findings','parrotfish, DNA barcoding, COI','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys EnvSci_0720760docx','','',NULL,'','','','0000-00-00','nn','','','','tes-0720760','tes-0720760',1,'NULL','',1,1,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2024-04-21','2024-04-21','2024-04-21 22:23:27','2024-07-19',NULL,'0000-00-00','Servet Dogdu*','',0,0,'',NULL,0,1,0,0,0,'','',''),(75,'Yakup Kutlu','yakupkutlu@gmail.com','','',0,0,'yakupkutlu@gmail.com','TEST Et quis et ut dolor ','',0,'In rerum harum harum','Commodi voluptatem ','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_tes-0759563.pdf','','../paperimages/image_0759563.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys EnvSci_0759563.docx','','','','0000-00-00','.','',' \r\n\r\nDear Corresponding Author,<br /> <br /> Please login the Journal Editorial Management System (<a href=&quot;https://www.tethysjournal.com&quot;>www.tethysjournal.com</a>) to check the proof of your M&S for publication in the Tethys Environmental Science. <br /><br />This is a final check and correction and you can only make small corrections.<br /> <br /> Please send us a list of corrections in the proof correction section in the  Journal Editorial Management System.<br /> <br /> Yours sincerely,<br /> <br /> Tethys Environmental Science Technical Team<br />Dr. Cemal Turan <br /> Editor  \r\n                ','','tes-0759563','tes-0759563',1,'Research Article','',1,1,0,0,-1,0,0,0,'2024-07-19','2024-04-22','2024-04-22 12:18:29','2024-07-18','2024-07-18','2024-07-18','Yakup Kutlu*','<br>yyyyyyyyyyyyy\r\n<br>yyyyyyyyyyyyyyy\r\n<br>yyyyyyyyyyyyyy',1,0,'111',111,2024,0,0,0,0,'10.5281/zenodo.13292766','13292766','{\"created\": \"2024-08-10T13:44:00.658954+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2024-08-10T13:44:00.696715+00:00\", \"id\": 13292766, \"conceptrecid\": \"13292765\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Et quis et ut dolor\", \"publication_date\": \"2024-07-18\", \"description\": \"In rerum harum harum\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Yakup Kutlu*\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Commodi voluptatem\"], \"references\": [\"