analyze similarities and assess the ability of the AI questions to classify both their output and the reference questions.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Yasemin  Atayolu *\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Yakup  Kutlu\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Question Classification\", \"Chatgpt\", \"Gemini\", \"Microsoft Copilot\", \"Bloom\'s Taxonomy\"], \"license\": \"cc-by-4.0\", \"journal_title\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"journal_volume\": \"1\", \"journal_issue\": \"2\", \"journal_pages\": \"87-98\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Zenodo\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.13138659\", \"recid\": 13138659}}, \"title\": \"Similarity and Classification Analysis in Turkish Question Generation of AI tools According to Bloom\'s Taxonomy\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13138659\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/ae68f05f-28fa-4957-8d49-a923221bda5c\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13138659\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13138659/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 13138659, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(105,'Yakup Kutlu','yakupkutlu@gmail.com','','',0,0,'yakupkutlu@gmail.com','test test testc','',0,'Repellendus Reprehe','Autem aute lorem vel','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_1051923.doc','','../paperimages/image_1051923.pptx',NULL,'','../uploadfiles/Approval_1051923.pdf','','0000-00-00','Corrupti illum dol','','','','TES-1051923','TES-1051923',0,'Technical Notes','',0,-1,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2024-07-27','2024-07-27','2024-07-27 13:08:28',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00','Yakup Kutlu*, Muhammed  Telceken , Kaan  Alptürk','',0,0,'',NULL,0,1,0,0,0,'','',''),(108,'Aybüke Uysal','aybukeuysal09@gmail.com','','',0,0,'aybukeuysal09@gmail.com','Expansion of the Invasive Moon Crab Matuta victor in Turkish Waters: A New Record from Mersin','',0,'In this study, a single female specimen of the moon crab, Matuta victor (Fabricius, 1781), was recorded in Erdemli, Akkum (Mersin) in May 2024. M. victor is a marine decapod species whose recent sightings in different regions and expanding distribution are increasingly reported. This paper mainly confirms its presence in Erdemli, Akkum (Mersin) and shares concerns about the possible ecological and economic impacts of its expanding presence along the Mediterranean coast of Turkey. The expanding distribution of M. victor suggests an urgent need to assess the invasion process of the species and its impact on the local ecosystem, as well as for studies based on continuous monitoring to understand the ecological impact of this species and develop effective management strategies. This study also provides distribution information on newly introduced species for conservation efforts to protect the local marine ecosystem.','Moon crab, matutidae, distribution, expansion, Gulf of Mersin, Türkiye','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1084649.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1084649.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1084649.png','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1084649.docx','','../uploadfiles/Approval_1084649.pdf','','0000-00-00','n','','','','TES-1084649','TES-1084649',1,'Research Article','',1,1,0,0