d arsenic speciation in the muscle tissue of Scyliorhinus canicula from the Mediterranean Sea. Bulletin of Environmental Contamination and Toxicology, 75(1).\r<br>TEG (2015). Turkish Environmental Guidelines 2015 Publications of Turkish Foundation of Environment\r<br>Turan F., Karan S., and Ergenler A. (2020). Effect of heavy metals on toxicogenetic damage of European eels Anguilla anguilla. Environmental Science and Pollution Research, 27(30), 38047-38055. \r<br>Turan, F., Yola, M. L., Ergenler, A., and Turan, C. (2021). The First Assessment on Metal Contamination in‎ the Critically Endangered Sawback Angel Shark ‎‎(Squatina aculeata) From North-Eastern‎ Mediterranean. Pakistan Journal of Marine Sciences, 30(2), 97-108.\r<br>Turan, C., Gürlek, M., Doğdu, S. A., Ergüden, D., Uyan, A., Ergenler, A., Soldo, A. (2024). Phylogenetic Relationships and Conservation Implications of Shark Species from Turkish Waters. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis Archives, 34 (1), 27-34.\r<br>US-EPA, (2004). Environmental Protection Agency-US, Integrated risk information system.\r<br>Vas, P. (1991). Trace metal levels in sharks from British and Atlantic waters. Marine Pollution bulletin, 22(2), 67-72.\r<br>Zheng, Q., Bao, C., Guo, W., Li, S., Chen, J., Chen, B., and Huang, S. (2016). Circular RNA profiling reveals an abundant circHIPK3 that regulates cell growth by sponging multiple miRNAs. Nature Communications, 7(1), 11215.',1,2,'105-116',105,2024,1,359,355,0,'10.5281/zenodo.13143427','13143427','{\"created\": \"2024-07-31T12:16:40.987828+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2024-07-31T12:16:41.038551+00:00\", \"id\": 13143427, \"conceptrecid\": \"13143426\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Trace Metal Induced Genotoxic Damage in Nursehound Shark, Scyliorhinus Stellaris, from The Northeastern Mediterranean\", \"publication_date\": \"2024-07-31\", \"description\": \"A rising number of contaminants in aquatic environments has led to significant concern  about environmental degradation, specifically its detrimental impacts on ecosystems and human wellness. The impact of trace metal pollution on aquatic ecosystems is an international issue. High levels of metals may lead to malignant and hazardous consequences in aquatic environments. This study focused on trace metal induced genotoxic damage in the Nursehound shark (Scyliorhinus stellaris) from Iskenderun Bay, the Northeastern Mediterranean. Samples were collected following established protocols according to recognized methods, and the detection of the trace elements was performed using the technique known as ICP-MS. The research applied the damage frequency (%), arbitrary unit (%), and genetic damage index (%) in S. stellaris to evaluate the extent of DNA damage resulting from pollutants. The amounts of Cd, Cr, Fe, Ni, Pb and Zn in the water columns at sample location were below Environmental Protection Agency, 2016 and Turkish Environmental Guideline, 2016. Trace metal concentrations in the liver tissue of S. stellaris were ranged as follows: Fe &gt; Zn&gt; Pb&gt;Cr&gt; Ni&gt;Cd for sampling site. According to our findings, the frequency of damage in the nursehound shark\'s gill and liver cells were 62.332\\u00b14.041% and 56.332\\u00b11.528%, accordingly. The gill tissue had a higher frequency of damage than the liver tissue. As a result, peresent study revealed, for the first time, the genotoxic damage of metal contamination in Nursehound shark S. stellaris in the Northeastern Mediterranean Sea.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Ay\\u015feg\\u00fcl Ergenler*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Funda Turan\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Shark\", \"DNA Damage\", \"Comet Assay\", \"Genotoxicity\", \"Scyliorhinus stellaris\"], \"license\": \"cc-by-4.0\", \"journal_title\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"journal_volume\": \"1\", \"journal_issue\": \"2\", \"journal_pages\": \"106-116\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Zenodo\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.13143427\", \"recid\": 13143427}}, \"title\": \"Trace Metal Induced Genotoxic Damage in Nursehound Shark, Scyliorhinus Stellaris, from The Northeastern Mediterranean\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13143427\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/9e6d24ad-41b2-4bf9-ac56-934fae742a77\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13143427\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13143427/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 13143427, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(110,'Muhammet Hakan Öncü','mhakanoncu@gmail.com','','',0,0,'mhakanoncu@gmail.com','Performance Comparison of Known AI Translation Tools for Turkish Language','',0,'Nowadays, artificial intelligence technologies are used in every field. One of these is translation tools for both academic and individual communication. These tools are used to communicate and transfer information by translating from Turkish to English and from English to Turkish. However, there is no detail about how accurate the translations made with these translation methods are. In this study, the English-Turkish translation performances of Google Translate, Amazon Translate and OpenAI GPT translation services were analyzed. After the translation process, the vector representations of the original Turkish texts and the Turkish texts obtained with the translation were compared. For this purpose, semantic similarity rates were obtained using Levenshtein distance and Cosine Similarity, and performance evaluation was made by considering the averages of these similarity rates and criteria such as time, cost and limitations. As a result, it is seen that Google Translate and Amazon Translate translation performance is more successful, but Google Transalate is seen as more affordable in terms of cost.','Translation Tools, Cosine Similarity, Levenshtein Distance, Semantic Similarity, Translation Performances','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1101525-R1.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1101525-R1.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1101525-R1.png','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1101525-R1.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1101525-R1.docx','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1101525-R1.docx','0000-00-00','.','','','','TES-1101525-R1','TES-1101525',1,'Research Article','',0,1,0,1,1,1,0,0,'2024-08-09','2024-06-30','2024-07-30 22:03:55','2024-08-08','2024-08-09','2024-09-30','Muhammet Hakan ÖNCÜ*, Yakup KUTLU','<br>Amazon. (2023a). Amazon Translate Documentation. https://docs.aws.amazon.com/translate/index.html\r<br>Amazon. (2023b). AWS Blog - Amazon Translate. https://aws.amazon.com/tr/blogs/machine-learning/translate-documents-in-real-time-with-amazon-translate/\r<br>Atayolu, Y., Kutlu, Y. (2024). Similarity and Classification Analysis in Turkish Question Generation of AI Tools According to Bloom’s Taxonomy. Tethys Environmental Science, 1(2), 87-98, doi : 10.5281/zenodo.13138659\r<br>Ayhan, B. (2023). Türkçe Duygu Analizi Veri Seti. https://huggingface.co/datasets/winvoker/turkish-sentiment-analysis-dataset\r<br>Aytan, B., & Sakar, C. O. (2022). Comparison of Transformer-Based Models Trained in Turkish and Different Languages on Turkish Natural Language Processing Problems. 2022 30th Signal Processing and Communications Applications Conference (SIU), 1–4.\r<br>Barmanbay, F. (2018). Turkish Product Reviews. https://github.com/fthbrmnby/turkish-text-data\r<br>Barut Evren. (2022). İstatistiksel Makine Çevirisi ile Nöral Makine Çevirisinin Dilbilimsel Parametrelerle Karşılaştırılması: Google Translate. Akdeniz Havzası ve Afrika Medeniyetleri Dergisi, 4(1), 103–118. Doi:10.54132/akaf.1116949\r<br>BERTurk. (2020a). dbmdz/bert-base-turkish-128k-uncased. https://huggingface.co/dbmdz/bert-base-turkish-128k-uncased\r<br>BERTurk. (2020b). software dbmdz/bert-base-turkish-cased. https://huggingface.co/dbmdz/bert-base-turkish-cased\r<br>Bilen, B. (2020). Duygu Analizi Veri Seti. https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/burhanbilenn/duygu-analizi-icin-urun-yorumlari\r<br>Brown, T. B., Mann, B., Ryder, N., Subbiah, M., Kaplan, J., Dhariwal, P., Neelakantan, A., Shyam, P., Sastry, G., Askell, A., Agarwal, S., Herbert-Voss, A., Krueger, G., Henighan, T., Child, R., Ramesh, A., Ziegler, D. M., Wu, J., Winter, C., … Amodei, D. (2020). Language Models are Few-Shot Learners (GPT-3). http://arxiv.org/abs/2005.14165\r<br>Çelikten, A., Bulut, H., & Onan, A. (2024). Biyomedikal literatürden solunum yolu hastalıkları ve semptom ilişkilerinin çıkarılması için semantik benzerlik temelli bir yaklaşım. Gazi Üniversitesi Mühendislik-Mimarlık Fakültesi Dergisi. https://doi.org/10.17341/gazimmfd.1354324\r<br>Gözen, G. (2022). A Comparative Study On The Performance Of Google Translate Between The Translation Of Different Text Types In The Light Of The Multidimensional Quality Metrics.\r<br>Keskin, M. (2018). Turkish Wikipedia Dump. https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mustfkeskin/turkish-wikipedia-dump/data\r<br>Levenshtein, V. I. (1966). Binary Codes Capable of Correcting Deletions, Insertions and Reversals. Soviet Physics Doklady, 10, 707–710.\r<br>OpenAI. (2023). OpenAI About. https://openai.com/about/\r<br>Radford, A., Wu, J., Child, R., Luan, D., Amodei, D., & Sutskever, I. (2019). Language Models are Unsupervised Multitask Learners (GPT-2). https://github.com/codelucas/newspaper\r<br>Reimers, N., & Gurevych, I. (2019, July). Sentence-BERT: Sentence Embeddings using Siamese BERT-Networks. Proceedings of the 2019 Conference on Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing. http://arxiv.org/abs/1908.10084\r<br>Subaşı, E. (2021). Turkish Tweets Sentiment Analysis. https://github.com/ezgisubasi/turkish-tweets-sentiment-analysis/tree/main/data\r<br>Tohma, K., & Kutlu, Y. (2020). Challenges Encountered in Turkish Natural Language Processing Studies. Natural and Engineering Sciences, 5(3), 204-211. Doi:10.28978/nesciences.833188\r<br>Tohma, K., Okur, H. I., Kutlu, Y., & Sertbas, A. (2023). Sentiment Analysis in Turkish Question Answering Systems: An Application of Human-Robot Interaction. IEEE Access, 11, 66522-66534\r<br>Ucan, A., Naderalvojoud, B., Sezer, E. A., & Sever, H. (2016). SentiWordNet for New Language: Automatic Translation Approach. 2016 12th International Conference on Signal-Image Technology & Internet-Based Systems (SITIS), 308–315. Doi:10.1109/SITIS.2016.57',1,3,'117-126',117,2024,1,683,492,0,'10.5281/zenodo.13269233','13269233','{\"created\": \"2024-08-08T09:16:01.583574+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2024-08-08T09:16:01.658071+00:00\", \"id\": 13269233, \"conceptrecid\": \"13269232\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Performance Comparison of Known AI Translation Tools for Turkish Language\", \"publication_date\": \"2024-08-08\", \"description\": \"Nowadays, artificial intelligence technologies are used in every field. One of these is translation tools for both academic and individual communication. These tools are used to communicate and transfer information by translating from Turkish to English and from English to Turkish. However, there is no detail about how accurate the translations made with these translation methods are. In this study, the English-Turkish translation performances of Google Translate, Amazon Translate and OpenAI GPT translation services were analyzed. After the translation process, the vector representations of the original Turkish texts and the Turkish texts obtained with the translation were compared. For this purpose, semantic similarity rates were obtained using Levenshtein distance and Cosine Similarity, and performance evaluation was made by considering the averages of these similarity rates and criteria such as time, cost and limitations.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Muhammet Hakan \\u00d6NC\\u00dc*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Yakup KUTLU\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Translation Tools\", \"Cosine Similarity\", \"Levenshtein Distance\", \"Semantic Similarity\", \"Translation Performances\"], \"license\": \"cc-by-4.0\", \"journal_title\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"journal_volume\": \"1\", \"journal_issue\": \"3\", \"journal_pages\": \"117-127\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Zenodo\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.13269233\", \"recid\": 13269233}}, \"title\": \"Performance Comparison of Known AI Translation Tools for Turkish Language\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13269233\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/d04d71bc-8652-4063-9f91-667800425916\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13269233\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13269233/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 13269233, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(111,'Çağdaş Can Cengiz','cagdascancengiz@gmail.com','','',0,0,'cagdascancengiz@gmail.com','Length-Weight Relationship of the Blackmouth Catshark (Galeus melastomus Rafinesque, 1810) on the Turkish Coasts of the Mediterranean Sea','',0,'This study investigates the relationship between the total length and body weight of the blackmouth catshark Galeus melastomus Rafinesque, 1810 sampled along the Mediterranean coast of Türkiye within the boundaries of the Geographical Sub-Area 24 during August and September 2023. A total of 336 individuals, 106 females and 230 males, were caught using bottom trawl. The total length and body weight of females range from 17.6 to 54.2 cm and 15.5 to 630 g, respectively. For males, the range is from 16.1 to 50.7 cm in length and from 13.0 to 426 g in weight. When considering both sexes together, the range is from 16.1 to 54.2 cm in length and from 13.0 to 630 g in weight. The average weight of males was calculated to be 169.43 ± 7.21 g with a standard error, while the average length of males was 36.96 ± 0.64 cm. Similarly, the average weight of females was 145.34 ± 15.67 g, and the average length of females was 32.32 ± 1.06 cm. The average length of all individuals without sex separation is 35.5 ± 0.56 cm, and the average weight is 161.83 ± 6.99 g. The length-weight relationship is determined as W = 0.002×L3.13 (r2 = 0.97) for females, W = 0.003×L2.94 (r2 = 0.98) for males, and W = 0.003×L3.00 (r2 = 0.98) for all individuals. The results obtained from this study are expected to contribute to filling the knowledge gap by highlighting the relationship between the length and weight of the blackmouth catshark in the examined area. It will also enable comparisons with other deep-sea locations in the Mediterranean Sea on this particular species.','Galeus melastomus, length-weight, body condition, eastern Mediterranean Sea','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1110851-R1.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1110851-R1.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1110851-R1.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1110851-R1.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1110851-R1.pdf','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1110851-R1.docx','0000-00-00','Dear Author(s),\r\nYour article has been accepted for publication. Thank you for choosing Tethys Environmental Science.\r\nSee you in new studies.','','','','TES-1110851-R1','TES-1110851',1,'NULL','',0,1,0,1,1,1,0,0,'2024-09-25','2024-08-02','2024-08-02 14:43:25','2024-09-06','2024-09-09','2024-09-30','Çağdaş Can Cengiz*, Coşkun Menderes Aydın, Aydın Ünlüoğlu, Sencer Akalın','<br>Abella, A., Serena, F., Mancusi, C., Ungaro, N., Hareide, N.-R., Guallart, J., Coelho, R.P. & Crozier, P. (2016). Galeus melastomus (Mediterranean assessment). The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2015: e.T161398A48915013. \r<br>Bottari, T., Rinelli, P., Ragonese, S. (2017). Investigating gear and seasonal effects in experimental trawl surveys: The case of Galeus melastomus Rafinesque, 1810 (Chondrichthyes, Scyliorhinidae) in the South of Sicily (Central Mediterranean). The Egyptian Journal of Aquatic Research, 43(1), 93-100. \r<br>Cabbar, K., Yığın, C. Ç. (2021). Length-weight relationships of Elasmobranch species from Gökçeada Island in the Northern Aegean Sea. Thalassas: An International Journal of Marine Sciences, 37(2), 497-504. \r<br>Carbonell, A., Alemany, F., Merella, P., Quetglas, A., Román, E. (2003). The by-catch of sharks in the western Mediterranean (Balearic Islands) trawl fishery. Fisheries Research, 61(1-3), 7-18\r<br>Darna, S. A., Bendiab, A. A. T., Mouffok, S., Belmahi, A. E., Bouderbala, M. (2018). Observation on distribution, biology, growth, diet and feeding strategy of blackmouth catshark Galeus melastomus (Rafi