e pelagic species, 14% are benthic species, 13% are rocky area species, 13% are shallow water and reef species, 11% are demersal species and 5% are other habitats, which are mainly distributed in the 0-100 m depth range.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Cemal Turan*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Deniz Erg\\u00fcden\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Mevl\\u00fct G\\u00fcrlek\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Servet Ahmet Do\\u011fdu\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Non-indigenous species\", \"Turkish marine waters\", \"distribution\", \"introduction pathways\"], \"references\": [\"\", \"TEST TEST Akamca, E., Mavruk, S., \\u00d6zyurt, C.E. and Kiyaga, V.B. (2011). First record of the Indo-Pacific burrowing goby Trypauchen vagina (Bloch and Schneider, 1801). in the North-Eastern Mediterranean Sea. Aquatic Invasion, 6, 19-21.\", \"Aksiray, F. (1954). T\\u00fcrkiye Deniz Baliklari Tayin Anahtari. Istanbul \\u00dcniversitesi Fen Fak\\u00fcltesi Hidrobiologi Arastirma Enstit\\u00fcs\\u00fc Yayinlari, Istanbul, 277 pp. (in Turkish)\", \"Aksiray, F. (1987). T\\u00fcrkiye Deniz Baliklari ve Tayin Anahtari. Istanbul \\u00dcniversitesi Rekt\\u00f6rl\\u00fcg\\u00fc Yayinlari, Istanbul, 811 pp .(in Turkish).\", \"Akyol, O., \\u00dcnal, V., Ceyhan, T. and Bilecenoglu, M. (2005). First confirmed record of Lagocephalus sceleratus (Gmelin, 1789). in the Mediterranean Sea. Journal of fish Biology, 66 (4), 1183-1186.\", \"Akyol, O., \\u00dcnal, V. and Ceyhan, T. (2006). Occurrence of two Lessepsian migrant fish, Oxyurichthys petersi (Gobiidae). and Upeneus pori (Mullidae), from the Aegean Sea. Cybium, 30 (4), 389-390.\", \"Akyol, O. and \\u00dcnal, V. (2013). Second record of the Cobia, Rachycentron canadum (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Rachycentridae), from The Mediterranean Sea. Acta Ichthyologica Et Piscatoria, 43 (4), 315-317.\", \"Akyol, O. and Ayd\\u0131n, \\u0130. (2016). A new record of Lagocephalus guentheri (Tetraodontiformes: Tetraodontidae). from the north-eastern Aegean Sea. Zoology in the Middle East, 62 (3), 271-273.\"], \"language\": \"eng\", \"license\": \"cc-by-4.0\", \"journal_title\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"journal_volume\": \"0\", \"journal_issue\": \"0\", \"journal_pages\": \"50-86\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"notes\": \"ISSN : 3023-7343\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.13292755\", \"recid\": 13292755}}, \"title\": \"TEST TEST TEST TEST TEST TEST TEST   Policy Support\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13292755\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/6d0dfd8a-d993-4f5d-aab8-ec3d86fa8e99\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/13292755\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/13292755/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 13292755, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(116,'Deniz   ERGUDEN','deniz.erguden@iste.edu.tr','','',0,0,'deniz.erguden@iste.edu.tr','Occurrence of the Indo-Pacific Stonefish, Synanceia verrucosa Bloch and Schneider, 1801 in the northeastern Mediterranean Sea','',0,'A single adult specimen of the stonefish, Synanceia verrucosa Bloch and Schneider, 1801, was observed on June 13, 2024, from Konacık (Iskenderun Bay), northeastern Mediterranean coast of Türkiye. The occurrence of this species in Turkish Mediterranean waters is probably due to its migration from the Red Sea via the Suez Canal. The present paper reports the second occurrence of the stonefish, S. verrucosa after thirteen years from the coast of Türkiye. Thus, this study is an important record that S. verrrucosa may have settled on the Northern Mediterranean coast of Türkiye.','Veneomous fish, synanceiidae, Iskenderun Bay, eastern Mediterranean, Türkiye','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1162599-R1.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1162599-R1.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1162599-R1.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1162599-R1.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1162599-R1.pdf','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1162599-R1.docx','0000-00-00','Dear authors,\r\n\r\nYour article &quot;Occurrence of the Indo-Pacific Stonefish, Synanceia verrucosa Bloch and Schneider, 1801 in the Northeastern Mediterranean&quot; has been accepted for publication.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nAli UYAN\r\nEditor','','','','TES-1162599-R1','TES-1162599',1,'Short Communications','',0,1,0,1,1,1,0,0,'2024-09-09','2024-07-25','2024-08-09 13:03:04','2024-09-07','2024-09-09','2024-09-30','Deniz Ergüden*, Cemal Turan, Sibel Alagöz Ergüden, Deniz Ayas ','<br>Abd Rabou, A.F.N., Elkahlout, K.E., Elnabris, K.J., Shurrab, H. M., Almalfouh, A. M., Baroud, A.F., Alattili, I.R., Aboutair, M.A. (2023). Rare records of the exotic Reef Stonefish (Synanceia verrucosa Bloch and Schneider, 1801) in the Mediterranean waters of the Gaza Strip, Palestine. International Journal of Fisheries and Biology Studies, 10(3), 24-28.\r<br>Akbora, H.D., Çiçek, B.A., Ayas, D. (2021). The first record of Synanceia verrucosa Bloch & Schneider, 1801 and Pagrus auriga Valenciennes, 1843 from Cyprus. Journal of Black Sea/Mediterranean Environment, 27(1), 109-116.\r<br>Bariche, M., Letourneur, Y., Harmelin-Vivien, M.