 Biologie Marine, 57(4), 335-342.\r<br>Pallaoro, A., Jardas, I., Santic, M. (2005). Weight-length relationships for 11 chondrichthyan species in the eastern Adriatic Sea. Cybium, 29(1), 93-96.\r<br>Ricker, W. E. (1975). Computation and interpretation of biological statistics of fish populations. The Blackburn Press.\r<br>Simpfendorfer, C. A., Kyne, P. M. (2009). Limited potential to recover from overfishing raises concerns for deep-sea sharks, rays and chimaeras. Environmental Conservation, 36(2), 97-103.\r<br>Sion, L., D Onghia, G., Tursi, A., Mytilineou, C. (2003). First data on distribution and biology of Squalus bainvillei (Risso, 1826) from the eastern Mediterranean Sea. Journal of Northwest Atlantic Fishery Science, 31, 213.\r<br>Sokal, R. R., Rohlf, F. J. (1987). Introduction to Biostatistics (2nd ed.). Dover Publications.\r<br>Turan, C., Ergenler, A., Doğdu, S. A., Turan, F. (2021). Age and growth of red sea goatfish, Parupeneus forsskali from Iskenderun Bay, Northeastern Mediterranean Sea. Journal of Ichthyology, 61, 758-763.\r<br>Turan, C., Gürlek, M., Doğdu, S. A., Ergüden, D., Uyan, A., Ergenler, A., Soldo, A. (2024). Phylogenetic relationships and conservation implications of shark species from Turkish waters. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis Archives, 34 (1), 27-34.\r<br>Uyan, A., Turan, C., Doğdu, S. A., Gürlek, M., Yağlıoğlu, D., Sönmez, B. (2024). Genetic and some bio-ecological characteristics of lessepsian lizardfish Saurida lessepsianus from the northeastern Mediterranean Sea. Tethys Environmental Science, 1(1), 1-16.\r<br>Yağlıoglu, D., Deniz, T., Gürlek, M., Ergüden, D., Turan, C. (2015). Elasmobranch bycatch in a bottom trawl fishery in the Iskenderun Bay, northeastern Mediterranean. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 56(3), 237-243.\r<br>Zar, J. H. (1999). Biostatistical Analysis (4th ed.). Prentice Hall.',1,4,'200-210',200,2024,1,499,387,0,'10.5281/zenodo.14293437','14293437','{\"created\": \"2024-12-07T11:28:41.069056+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2024-12-07T11:28:41.115528+00:00\", \"id\": 14293437, \"conceptrecid\": \"14293436\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Evidence of Nursery Area and Length-Weight Relationships for Longnose Spurdog Squalus blainville in the Eastern Mediterranean\", \"publication_date\": \"2024-12-15\", \"description\": \"Nursery areas are essential habitats for sharks, offering protection and increasing the survival of newborns. This study aims to investigate a potential nursery area for Squalus blainville in the Eastern Mediterranean Sea that has very scarce information in the eastern Mediterranean Sea and contributes to the length-weight relationships. We identified the location of the potential nursery area by interviewing local fishermen. We collected 48 adults and 22 embryos neonates of S. blainville specimens from the entrance of Iskenderun Bay on 03 April 2024. We recorded 48 longnose spurdog sharks in the catches ranging from 68.9 cm to 120.2 cm TL, which corresponded to mature individuals. The length-weight relations (LWR) of combined sexes of S. blainville were observed as W = 0.0005 x L3.0277 (R2 = 0.9303). Our data provide evidence to recognize Iskenderun Bay as a possible nursery area for longnose spurdog sharks, meeting all the criteria proposed to identify nursery areas. These findings constitute the first documented evidence of a longnose spurdog shark nursery area in the Iskenderun Bay in Turkish marine waters.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Cemal Turan*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Servet A. Do\\u011fdu\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Alen Soldo\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Longnose spurdog\", \"Nursery area\", \"Iskenderun Bay\", \"length-weight relationship\"], \"references\": [\"\", \"Akyol, O., \\u015een, H. (2022). Recent observations on sandbar shark Carcharhinus plumbeus (Carchardinidae) around sea cages of fish farms in Iskenderun Bay (T\\u00fcrkiye, Eastern Mediterranean Sea). Journal of the Black Sea/