ulation. In morphological analyses, 16 morphometric and 6 meristic characters were used. According to Canonical Discriminant Function Analysis, the first discriminant function expressed 100% of the total variation. According to the PCA, the first principal component accounted for 23.4% of the total variation and the second principal component accounted for 16.03% of the total variation. The present study revealed the genetic and morphologic differentiation coupled with low genetic diversity at the margins of the geographical separation of B. belone in Bulgaria and Turkish marine waters. Therefore, The Bulgarian and Turkish sides should consider urgent mutual management measures for the conservation of B. belone populations in Bulgarian and Turkish marine waters.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Cemal Turan*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Petya Pavlova Ivanova\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Servet Ahmet Do\\u011fdu\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Deniz Erg\\u00fcden\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Violin Stoyanov Raykov\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Maria Yankova\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Deniz Ya\\u011flio\\u011flu\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Ay\\u015feg\\u00fcl Ergenler\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Ivelina Zlateva\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Nina Stoycheva Dzhembekova2\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Belone belone\", \"garfish\", \"population genetic\", \"black sea\", \"mtDNA COI\"], \"references\": [\"\", \"Avise, J. C., Arnold, J., Ball, R. M., Bermingham, E., Lamb, T., Neigel, J. E., Saunders, N. C. (1987). Intraspecific phylogeography: the mitochondrial DNA bridge between population genetics and systematics. Annual Review of Ecology and Systematics, 489-522.\", \"Begg, G. A., Friedland, K. D., Pearce, J. B. (1999). Stock identification and its role in stock assessment and fisheries management: an overview. Fisheries Research, 43(1-