": \"6-11\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"notes\": \"ISSN : 3023-7343\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.15007131\", \"recid\": 15007131}}, \"title\": \"Occurrence of the Sponge Crab Dromia personata (Linnaeus, 1758) from the Mersin Bay, Northeastern Mediterranean\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/15007131\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/dea33b00-7170-4c31-aa4d-f5aaa745e842\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/15007131\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15007131/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 15007131, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(128,'WAHID REFES','wahid.refes@enssmal.edu.dz','','',0,0,'wahid.refes@enssmal.edu.dz','Inventory of Marine Molluscs in the Taza National Park of Algeria in the western Mediterranean','',0,'In the marine section of Taza National Park on the Algerian coasts in the western Mediterranean, 97 species of molluscs have been documented comprising 37 bivalves, 48 gastropods, one polyplacophoran and 11 cephalopods. The main families are Donacidae with Donax trunculus as the main species (10.59% of bivalves populations) and Nassariidae with Rissoae membrancea as the main species (14.46% of gastropods populations).This includes the discovery of five species new to the Algerian coast, all belonging to the class Gastropoda: Felimare picta (R.A. Philippi, 1836), Felimida luteorosea (Rapp, 1827), Felimida purpurea (Risso,1831), Platydoris argo (Linnaeus, 1767) and Antiopella cristata (Delle Chiaje, 1841). This specific richness represents 23.72% of the malacological richness recorded along the Algerian coast of which bivalves, gastropods, polyplacophores and cephalopods represent 18.14%, 30.38%, 0.80% and 30.56% of the respective specific richness of the different classes of molluscs of the Algerian coast.','Check-list, Marine molluscs, Taza National Park, Algeria, western Mediterranean','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1281398-R2.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1281398-R2.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1281398-R2.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1281398-R2.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1281398-R2.pdf','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1281398-R2.doc','0000-00-00','Dear authors, we are pleased to inform you that your article has been accepted for publication in its final version. We appreciate your selection of Tethys Environmental Sciences.','','','','TES-1281398-R2','TES-1281398',1,'Research Article','',0,1,0,2,1,1,0,0,'2024-12-02','2024-09-25','2024-09-25 14:03:29','2024-10-15','2024-11-24','2024-12-15','Nahla Lahmer, Wahid Refes*','<br>Amar, Y. (1998). Etude des peuplements macrobenthiques du golfe d’Arzew. Institute of Marine Sciences and Coastal Management. Algiers, p 215. \r<br>Bakalem, A. (2008). Contribution à l’étude des peuplements benthiques du plateau continental algérien. Houari Boumediene University of Science and Technology. Algiers, p 678.\r<br>Bakalem, A., Hily, C., Romano, J.C. (1981). Contribution à l’étude des peuplements benthiques de la Baie d’Alger : Cartographie et définition des peuplements. Pelagos 6(2), 8-111.\r<br>Bouchet, P., Ortea, J. (1980). Quelques Chromod