rnal Aquatic. Biolology, 8(3), 224-227.\r<br>Nordsieck, F. (1982). Die Europäischen Meeresmuscheln (Bivalvia). Gustav Fischer Verlag.\r<br>Oulmi, Y. (1991). Contribution à l&#39;étude des peuplements macrozoobenthiques de la baie de BouIsmaïl: Secteur Ouest. Mémoire de magister en océanographie biologique. ISMAL.\r<br>Pallary, P. (1900). Coquille marines du littoral du département d’Oran. Journal de Conchyliologie, 48(1), 211-428\r<br>Parenzan, P. (1974). Carta d’identità delle conchiglie del Mediterraneo. Bivalvi, ii parte. Bios Taras Publisher.\r<br>Petit, J.M. (1972). Contribution à l&#39;étude du peuplement benthique de la baie d&#39;Alger. Pelagos, 4(1), 37-69.\r<br>PNT/ISMAL. (2003). Plan de gestion de la zone marine située entre Cap Afia et la limite administrative Jijel-Béjaïa (Wilaya de Jijel) : Approches descriptives et analytiques de la zone marine – Evaluation du patrimoine et définition des objectifs – Plan de travail. Rapport final de la convention Parc National de Taza et Institut National des Sciences de la Mer et de l’Aménagement du Littoral, p314.\r<br>PNUE/PAM-CAR/ASP. (2018). Protocole ASP/DB: Annexe II: Liste des espèces en danger ou menacées. Available at: https://www.rac-spa.org/sites/default/files/annex/annex_2_fr_20182.pdf \r<br>Poutiers, J.M. (1987). Bivalves (Acephales, Lamellibranches, Pelecypodes). In Fiches FAO d’identification des espèces pour les besoins de la pêche (pp. 369-512). FAO.',1,4,'179-192',179,2024,1,397,521,0,'10.5281/zenodo.14196289','14196289','{\"created\": \"2024-11-21T08:59:07.902414+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2024-11-21T08:59:07.967101+00:00\", \"id\": 14196289, \"conceptrecid\": \"14196288\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Inventory of Marine Molluscs in the Taza National Park (Eastern Algeria)\", \"publication_date\": \"2024-12-15\", \"description\": \"In the marine section of Taza National Park, 97 species of molluscs have been documented comprising 37 bivalves, 48 gastropods, one polyplacophoran and 11 cephalopods. The main families are Donacidae with Donax trunculus as the main species (10.59% of bivalves populations) and Nassariidae with Rissoae membrancea as the main species (14.46% of gastropods populations).This includes the discovery of five species new to the Algerian coast, all belonging to the class Gastropoda: Felimare picta (R.A. Philippi, 1836), Felimida luteorosea (Rapp, 1827), Felimida purpurea (Risso,1831), Platydoris argo (Linnaeus, 1767) and Antiopella cristata (Delle Chiaje, 1841). This specific richness represents 23.72% of the malacological richness recorded along the Algerian coast of which bivalves, gastropods, polyplacophores and cephalopods represent 18.14%, 30.38%, 0.80% and 30.56% of the respective specific richness of the different classes of molluscs of the Algerian coast.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Nahla Lahmer\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Wahid Refes*\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Inventory\", \"Marine molluscs\", \"Taza National Park\", \"Algeria\", \"western Mediterranean\"], \"references\": [\"\", \"Amar, Y. (1998). Etude des peuplements macrobenthiques du golfe d\'Arzew. Institute of Marine Sciences and Coastal Management. Algiers, p 215.\", \"Bakalem, A. (2008). Contribution \\u00e0 l\'\\u00e9tude des peuplements benthiques du plateau continental alg\\u00e9rien. Houari Boumediene University of Science and Technology. Algiers, p 678.\", \"Bakalem, A., Hily, C., Romano, J.C. (1981). Contribution \\u00e0 l\'\\u00e9tude des peuplements benthiques de la Baie d\'Alger : Cartographie et d\\u00e9finition des peuplements. Pelagos 6(2), 8-111.\", \"Bouchet, P., Ortea, J. (1980). Quelques Chromodorididae bleus (Mollusca, gastropoda, Nudibranchiata) de l\'Atlantique oriental. Annales Institut Oc\\u00e9anographique, 56(2), 117-125.\", \"Christiaens, J. (1973). R\\u00e9vision du genre Patella (Mollusca, Gasteropoda). Bulletin Mus\\u00e9um national d\'histoire naturelle, 182(121), 1305-1392.\", \"Dautz