\\u0130. B. (2023). Age, Growth and Reproduction of the Thornback ray, Raja clavata (Linnaeus, 1758) in the Waters Off G\\u00f6k\\u00e7eada (the Northern Aegean Sea). Thalassas: An International Journal of Marine Sciences, 39(2), 943-951.\", \"Zenetos, A., Gofas, S., Verlaque, M., \\u00c7\\u0131nar, M., Garcia-Raso, J., Bianchi, C., Morri, C., Azzurro, E., Bi\\u0307leceno\\u011flu, M., Froglia, C., Siokou, I., Violanti, D., Sfriso, A., San Martin, G., Giangrande, A., Kata\\u011fan, T., Ballesteros, E., Ramos-Espla, A., Mastrototaro, F. Ocana, O., Zingone, A., Gambi, M., Streftaris, N. (2010). Alien Species in the Mediterranean Sea by 2010. A Contribution to the Application of European Union\'s Marine Strategy Framework Directive (MSFD). Part I. Spatial Distribution. Mediterranean Marine Science, 11(2), 381.\"], \"language\": \"eng\", \"license\": \"cc-by-4.0\", \"journal_title\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"journal_volume\": \"2\", \"journal_issue\": \"1\", \"journal_pages\": \"31-61\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"notes\": \"ISSN : 3023-7343\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.15032119\", \"recid\": 15032119}}, \"title\": \"Checklist of Cartilaginous Species with Current Status and Conservation Strategies in Turkish Marine Waters\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/15032119\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/df9b46d8-5748-440f-865b-62836391a218\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/15032119\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15032119/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 15032119, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(132,'Deniz Ayas','ayasdeniz@gmail.com','','',0,0,'ayasdeniz@gmail.com','Sand Steenbras Lithognathus mormyrus (Linnaeus, 1758), the New Host of the Parasitic Isopod Anilocra physodes (Linnaeus, 1758) from Mersin Bay, Northeastern Mediterranean','',0,'Anilocra physodes (Linnaeus, 1758) (Isopoda, Cymothoidae) was reported for the first time in this study on a new host species, Lithognathus mormyrus (Linnaeus, 1758) (Pisces; Sparidae), from Mersin Bay, northeastern Mediterranean, Türkiye. Besides, some morphological characteristics of this parasitic isopod were demonstrated and its differences from the closely related species A. frontalis are highlighted. The present study revealed the detailed distribution of host species of A. physodes in Turkish marine waters by their families and host preferences.','Anilocra, Cymothoidae, Parasitic Isopod, Lithognathus mormyrus, Mersin Bay.','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1326778-R1.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1326778-R1.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1326778-R1.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1326778-R1.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1326778-R1.docx','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci_TES-1326778-R1.docx','0000-00-00','Dear authors, we are pleased to inform you that your article has been accepted for publication in its final version. We appreciate your selection of Tethys Environmental Sciences.','','','','TES-1326778-R1','TES-1326778',1,'Research Article','',0,1,0,1,1,1,0,0,'2024-12-08','2024-10-26','2024-11-07 06:49:21','2024-12-06','2024-12-07','2024-12-15','Caf