//zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15296604/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15296604/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15296604/actions/newversion\", \"registerconceptdoi\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15296604/actions/registerconceptdoi\"}, \"record_id\": 15296604, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(138,'Deniz   ERGUDEN','deniz.erguden@iste.edu.tr','','',0,0,'deniz.erguden@iste.edu.tr','Rare Occurrence of the Rough Ray Raja radula (Family: Rajidae) in the Northeastern Mediterranean','',0,'On December 04, 2017, a single female specimen of rough ray Raja radula Delaroche 1809 with a total length of 510 mm and weight of 780 g, and its egg case were caught by a commercial trawler from a 65-80 m depth range.  R. radula is endemic to the Mediterranean and is a rare species in terms of its occurrence on the eastern Mediterranean coast of Türkiye. Therefore, the present study reports a rare occurrence of R. radula and its egg case off Aydıncık, Mersin Bay (northeastern Mediterranean) along with some of their morphological measurements. The species is a high priority for conservation action, and urgent plans must be made and implemented without delay to protect this species, which is approaching critical levels.','Rare occurrence, rough ray, Raja radula, Mersin Bay, northeastern Mediterranean','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1386843-R1.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1386843-R1.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1386843-R1.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1386843-R1.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1386843-R1.pdf','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1386843-R1.docx','0000-00-00','Dear authors, we are pleased to inform you that your article has been accepted for publication in its final version. We appreciate your selection of Tethys Environmental Sciences.','',''