": \"16-28\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"notes\": \"ISSN : 3023-7343\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.15662742\", \"recid\": 15662742}}, \"title\": \"Predicting Air Quality Index Based on Rainfall Patterns: A Machine Learning Approach with Mathematical Modelling\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15662742\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/15662742\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15662742/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/bfb2c6c4-83a2-464b-b09c-16aaf4656300\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15662742\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/15662742\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15662742/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15662742/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15662742/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/15662742/actions/newversion\"}, \"record_id\": 15662742, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(142,'Servet Dogdu','dogduservet@gmail.com','','',0,0,'dogduservet@gmail.com','Additional Record of Pelagic Tunicate Pyrosoma atlanticum Péron, 1804 from Mersin Bay, Northeastern Mediterranean','',0,'Pyrosomes, belonging to the Pyrosomatidae family, are pelagic, colonial tunicates composed of thousands of zooids within a common, gelatinous tunic. They are known for their long-lived bioluminescence and occasional large-scale blooms. Pyrosoma atlanticum Peron, 1804 is the only representative of pyrosomes in the Mediterranean. On 9 February 2025, a single colony of P. atlanticum was observed during a scuba dive at a depth of 12 m in Mersin Bay, Türkiye. The present study reports an additional record for the pelagic tunicate P. atlanticum in the northeastern Mediterranean.','Pyrosomes, Pyrosoma atlanticum, additional record, Mersin Bay, Türkiye','Engineering Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1420628-R1.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1420628-R1.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1420628-R1.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1420628-R1.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1420628-R1.docx','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1420628-R1.docx','0000-00-00','Dear authors, we are pleased to inform you that your article has been accepted for publication in its final version. We appreciate your selection of Tethys Environmental Sciences.','','','','TES-1420628-R1','TES-1420628',1,'Research Article','',0,1,0,1,1,1,0,0,'2025-06-23','2025-03-29','2025-05-29 13:44:51','2025-05-11','2025-06-21','2025-06-23','Ali Uyan*, Necdet Uyğur, Ayşegül Ergenler, Servet Ahmet Doğdu','<br>Alldredge, A. L., Madin, L. P. (1982). Pelagic tunicates: unique herbivores in the marine plankton. Bioscience, 32(8), 655-663.\r<br>Andersen, V., Sardou, J., Nival, P. (1992). The diel migrations and vertical distributions of zooplankton and micronekton in the Northwestern Mediterranean Sea. 2. Siphonophores, hydromedusae and pyrosomids. Journal of Plankton Research, 14(8), 1155-1169.\r<br>Angel, M. V. (1989). Vertical profiles of pelagic communities in the vicinity of the Azores Front and their implications to deep ocean ecology. Progress in Oceanography, 22(1), 1-46.\r<br>Archer, S. K., Kahn, A. S., Leys, S. P., Norgard, T., Girard, F., Du Preez, C., Dunham, A. (2018). Pyrosome consumption by benthic organisms during blooms in the northeast Pacific and Gulf of Mexico. Ecology, 99, 981-984.\r<br>Bellido, J. J., Baez, J. C., Souviron-Priego, L., Ferri-Yanez, F., Salas, C., López, J. A., Real, R. (2020). Atmospheric indices allow anticipating the incidence of jellyfish coastal swarms. Mediterranean Marine Science, 21(2), 289-297.\r<br>Brissimi,