., Thurston, M. H., Tyler, P. A. (1987). Great Meteor East: a biological characterisation. Institute of Oceanographic Sciences Deacon Laboratory.\r<br>Sardou, J., Etienne, M., Andersen, V. (1996). Seasonal abundance and vertical distributions of macroplankton and micronekton in the Northwestern Mediterranean Sea. Oceanologica Acta, 19(6), 645-656.\r<br>Stenvers, V. I., Hauss, H., Osborn, K. J., Neitzel, P., Merten, V., Scheer, S., Robison, B. H., Freitas, R., Hoving, H. J. T. (2021). Distribution, associations and role in the biological carbon pump of Pyrosoma atlanticum (Tunicata, Thaliacea) off Cabo Verde, NE Atlantic. Scientific Reports, 11(1), 9231.\r<br>van der Land, J., van Soest, R. W. M. (2001). Thaliacea. In European Register of Marine Species: A Check-list of the Marine Species in Europe and A Bibliography of Guides to Their Identification (pp. 355-356). Collection Patrimoines Naturels.\r<br>van Soest, R. W. M. (1981). A monograph of the order Pyrosomatida (Tunicata, Thaliacea). Journal of Plankton Research, 3(4), 603-631.\r<br>Weikert, H., Godeaux, J. E. (2008). Thaliacean distribution and abundance in the northern part of the Levantine Sea (Crete and Cyprus) during the eastern Mediterranean climatic transient, and a comparison with the western Mediterranean basin. Helgoland Marine Research, 62, 377-387.\r<br>WoRMS (2025). Pyrosoma Péron, 1804. World Register of Marine Species. Available at: https://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=137224 (10.03.2025).',2,2,'104-110',104,2025,1,275,338,0,'10.5281/zenodo.15710687','15710687','{\"created\": \"2025-06-21T10:59:50.812485+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2025-06-21T10:59:50.883060+00:00\", \"id\": 15710687, \"conceptrecid\": \"15710686\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Additional Record of Pelagic Tunicate Pyrosoma atlanticum P\\u00e9ron, 1804 from Mersin Bay, Northeastern Mediterranean\", \"publication_date\": \"2025-06-23\", \"description\": \"Pyrosomes, belonging to the Pyrosomatidae family, are pelagic, colonial tunicates composed of thousands of zooids within a common, gelatinous tunic. They are known for their long-lived bioluminescence and occasional large-scale blooms. Pyrosoma atlanticum Peron, 1804 is the only representative of pyrosomes in the Mediterranean. On 9 February 2025, a single colony of P. atlanticum was observed during a scuba dive at a depth of 12 m in Mersin Bay, T\\u00fcrkiye. The present study reports an additional record for the pelagic tunicate P. atlanticum in the northeastern Mediterranean.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Ali Uyan*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Necdet Uy\\u011fur\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Ay\\u015feg\\u00fcl Ergenler\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Servet Ahmet Do\\u011fdu\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Pyrosomes\", \"Pyrosoma atlanticum\", \"additional record\", \"Mersin Bay\", \"T\\u00fcrkiye\"], \"references\": [\"\", \"Alldredge, A. L., Madin, L. P. (1982). Pelagic tunicates: unique herbivores in the marine plankton. Bioscience, 32(8), 655-663.\", \"Andersen, V., Sardou, J., Nival, P. (1992). The diel migrations and vertical distributions of zooplankton and micronekton in the Northwestern Mediterranean Sea. 2. Siphonophores, hydromedusae and pyrosomids. Journal of Plankton Research, 14(8), 1155-1169.\", \"Angel, M. V. (1989). Vertical profiles of pelagic communities in the vicinity of the Azores Front and their implications to deep ocean ecology. Progress in Oceanography, 22(1), 1-46.\", \"Archer, S. K., Kahn, A. S., Leys, S. P., Norgard, T., Girard, F., Du Preez, C., Dunham, A. (2018). Pyrosome consumption by benthic organisms during blooms in the northeast Pacific and Gulf of Mexico. Ecology, 99, 981-984.\", \"Bellido, J. J., Baez, J. C., Souviron-Priego, L., Ferri-Yanez, F., Salas, C., L\\u00f3pez, J. A., Real, R. (2020). Atmospheric indices allow anticipating the incidence of jellyfish coastal swarms. Mediterranean Marine Science, 21(2), 289-297.\", \"Brissimi, C., Pantelidou, M., Kallianiotis, A. A., Vidoris, P., Antoniadou, C., Anastasiadou, C. (2024). Notes on Pyrosoma atlanticum P\\u00e9ron, 1804 with a revision of the deep-sea taxon in the Mediterranean basin. Oceanography Fisheries Open Access Journal, 17(3), 555970.\", \"Brodeur, R. D., Perry, I., Boldt, J., Flostrand, L., Galbraith, M., King, J., Murphy, J., Sakuma, K., Thompson, A. (2018). An unusual gelatinous plankton event in the NE Pacific: the great pyrosome bloom of 2017. PICES Press, 26(1), 22-27.\", \"Brodeur, R. D., Buckley, T. W., Lang, G. M., Draper, D. L., Buchanan, J. C., Hibpshman, R. E. (2021). Demersal fish predators of gelatinous zooplankton in the Northeast Pacific Ocean. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 658, 89-104.\", \"Carvalho, P. F., Bonecker, S. L. C. (2008). Tunicata, Thaliacea, Pyrosomatidae, Pyrosomella verticillata (Neumann, 1909): first record from the Southwest Atlantic Ocean. Check List, 4(3), 272-274.\", \"Decima, M., Stukel, M. R., L\\u00f3pez\\u2010L\\u00f3pez, L., Landry, M. R. (2019). The unique ecological role of pyrosomes in the Eastern Tropical Pacific. Limnology and Oceanography, 64(2), 728-743.\", \"Drits, A. V., Arashkevich, E. G., Semenova, T. N. (1992). Pyrosoma atlanticum (Tunicata, Thaliacea): grazing impact on phytoplankton standing stock and role in organic carbon flux. Journal of Plankton Research, 14(6), 799-809.\", \"Galil, B. S., Goren, M. (1994). The deep sea Levantine fauna. New records and rare occurrences. Senckenbergiana Maritima, 25, 41-52.\", \"Gibbons, M. J., Gugushe, N., Boyd, A. J., Shannon, L. J., Mitchell-Innes, B. A. (1999). Changes in the composition of the non-copepod zooplankton assemblage in St Helena Bay (southern Benguela ecosystem) during a six day drogue study. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 180, 111-120.\", \"Godeaux, J., Bone, Q., Braconnot, J. C. (1998). Anatomy of Thaliacea. In The Biology of Pelagic Tunicates (pp. 1-24). Oxford Academic.\", \"G\\u00f6n\\u00fclal, O.,