-Relini, L. (2021). Atlas of Exotic Fishes in the Mediterranean Sea (2nd edition). CIESM Publishers.\r<br>Goren, M., Lipsky, G., Brokovich, E., Abelson, A. (2010). A ‘Flood’ of Alien Cardinal Fishes in the Eastern Mediterranean – First Record of the Indo-Pacific Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (Rüpell, 1838) in the Mediterranean Sea. Aquatic Invasions, 5 (Suppl. 1), 49-51.\r<br>Irmak, E., Engin, S. (2015). A Newly Established Population of the Indian Ocean Twospot Cardinalfish, Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (Rüppell, 1838), in the Northern Levantine Sea (Osteichthyes: Apogonidae). Zoology in the Middle East, 61(2), 186-188.\r<br>Karakulak, F. S., Gökoğlu, M., Uzer, U., Kabasakal, H. (2024a). First Record of the Abudefduf cf. saxatilis/vaigiensis/troschelii Species Complex (Pisces: Pomacentridae), in the Black Sea. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 34, 205-210.\r<br>Karakulak, F. S., Gökoğlu, M., Uzer, U., Kabasakal, H. (2024b). First Record of Goldblotch Grouper, Epinephelus costae (Steindachner, 1878) (Family: Serranidae) from the Sea of Marmara. Aquatic Sciences and Engineering, 40, 30-32.\r<br>Langeneck, J., Bakiu, R., Chalari, N., Chatzigeorgiou, G., Crocetta, F., Doğdu, S.A., Durmishaj, S., Galil, B. S., García-Charton, J. A., Gülşahin, A., Hoffman, R., Leone, A., Lezzi, M., Logrieco, A., Mancini, E., Minareci, E., Petović, S., Ricci, P., Orenes-Salazar, V., Sperone, E., Spinelli, A., Stern, N., Tagar, A., Tanduo, V., Taşkın, E., Tiralongo, F., Trainito, E., Turan, C., Yapıcı, S., Zafeiridis, I., Zenetos, A. (2023). New records of introduced species in the Mediterranean Sea (November 2023). Mediterranean Marine Science, 24(3), 610-632. \r<br>Myers, P., Espinosa, R., Parr, C. S., Jones, T., Hammond, G. S., Dewey, T. A. (2025). The Animal Diversity Web (online). Accessed at: https://animaldiversity.org (25.08.2025).\r<br>Rothman, B. S. S., Goren, M., Galil, B. S. (2013). Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (Rüppell, 1838) Along the Levantine Coast of the Mediterranean Sea: A Forthcoming Invasion? BioInvasions Records, 2, 85-88. \r<br>Turan, C., Ergüden, D., Uygur, N., Gürlek, M., Erdoğan, Z. A., Sonmez, B., Uyan, A., Karan, S., Doğdu S. A. (2015). First record of the Indian Ocean twospot cardinalfish, Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Apogonidae), from Turkish marine waters. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 45(3), 319-322.',2,3,'111-115',111,2025,1,93,93,0,'10.5281/zenodo.17064449','17064449','{\"created\": \"2025-09-05T16:14:25.143078+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2025-09-05T16:14:25.232808+00:00\", \"id\": 17064449, \"conceptrecid\": \"17064448\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"Additional Record of Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (R\\u00fcppell, 1838) from the Aegean Sea (G\\u00f6kova Bay, T\\u00fcrkiye)\", \"description\": \"On 23 July 2025, the schools of Cheilodiperus novemstriatus associated with three black longspine urchins (Diadema setosum) over a hard substrate in the shoreline of Akb\\u00fck, G\\u00f6kova Bay were observed during snorkeling. The depth of the substrate was recorded as 1 m. This ichthyological note presents the second record of C. novemstriatus from the southeastern Aegean Sea. Since 2010, the species has been documented in eight different locations, and ongoing westward and northward spread.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Hasan Tarun\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"O\\u011fuzhan Tak\\u0131cak\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Okan Akyol*\", \"affiliation\": null}], \"keywords\": [\"Cheilodipterus novemstriatus\", \"additional record\", \"snorkelling\", \"southeastern Aegean Sea\", \"G\\u00f6kova Bay\"], \"references\": [\"\", \"Bariche, M., Azzurro, E. (2012). New Records and Establishment of the Indian Ocean Twospot Cardinalfish Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (R\\u00fcppell, 1838) in the Mediterranean Sea. BioInvasions Records, 1(4), 299-301.\", \"Bileceno\\u011flu, M., Yoke\\u015f, M. B., Draman, M. (2019). The Invasive Sea Urchin Diadema setosum Provides Shelter for Coastal Fish \\u2013 First Observations from the Mediterranean Sea. Zoology in the Middle East, 65(2), 183-185.\", \"Crocetta, F., Agius, D., Balistreri, P., Bariche, M., Bayhan, Y. K., \\u00c7ak\\u0131r, M., Ciriaco, S., Corsini-Foka, M., Deidun, A., El Zrelli, R., Erg\\u00fcden, D., Evans, J., Ghelia, M., Giavasi, M., Kleitou, P., Kondylatos, G., Lipej, L., Mifsud, C., \\u00d6zvarol, Y., Pagano, A., Portelli, P., Poursanidis, D., Rabaoui, L., Schembri, P.J., Ta\\u015fkin, E., Tiralongo, F., Zenetos, A. (2015). New Mediterranean Biodiversity Records (October 2015). Mediterranean Marine Science, 16(3), 682-702.\", \"\\u00c7i\\u00e7ek, B. A., Akbora, D., Ayas, D. (2020). Does Symbiosis of Invasive Species Become Common Phenomena for the Mediterranean? Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (R\\u00fcppell 1838) and Diadema setosum (Leske 1778) is Observed Together in the Gulf of Iskenderun. Journal of Wildlife and Biodiversity, 4 (Special issue), 13-18.\", \"Froese, R., Pauly, D. (2025). FishBase. World Wide Web electronic publication. www.fishbase.org, version (04/2025).\", \"Golani, D., Azzuro, E., Dulcic, J., Massuti, E., Orsi-Relini, L. (2021). Atlas of Exotic Fishes in the Mediterranean Sea (2nd edition). CIESM Publishers.\", \"Goren, M., Lipsky, G., Brokovich, E., Abelson, A. (2010). A \'Flood\' of Alien Cardinal Fishes in the Eastern Mediterranean \\u2013 First Record of the Indo-Pacific Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (R\\u00fcpell, 1838) in the Mediterranean Sea. Aquatic Invasions, 5 (Suppl. 1), 49-51.\", \"Irmak, E., Engin, S. (2015). A Newly Established Population of the Indian Ocean Twospot Cardinalfish, Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (R\\u00fcppell, 1838), in the Northern Levantine Sea (Osteichthyes: Apogonidae). Zoology in the Middle East, 61(2), 186-188.\", \"Karakulak, F. S., G\\u00f6ko\\u011flu, M., Uzer, U., Kabasakal, H. (2024a). First Record of the Abudefduf cf. saxatilis/vaigiensis/troschelii Species Complex (Pisces: Pomacentridae), in the Black Sea. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 34, 205-210.\", \"Karakulak, F. S., G\\u00f6ko\\u011flu, M., Uzer, U., Kabasakal, H. (2024b). First Record of Goldblotch Grouper, Epinephelus costae (Steindachner, 1878) (Family: Serranidae) from the Sea of Marmara. Aquatic Sciences and Engineering, 40, 30-32.\", \"Langeneck, J., Bakiu, R., Chalari, N., Chatzigeorgiou, G., Crocetta, F., Do\\u011fdu, S.A., Durmishaj, S., Galil, B. S., Garc\\u00eda-Charton, J. A., G\\u00fcl\\u015fahin, A., Hoffman, R., Leone, A., Lezzi, M., Logrieco, A., Mancini, E., Minareci, E., Petovi\\u0107, S., Ricci, P., Orenes-Salazar, V., Sperone, E., Spinelli, A., Stern, N., Tagar, A., Tanduo, V., Ta\\u015fk\\u0131n, E., Tiralongo, F., Trainito, E., Turan, C., Yap\\u0131c\\u0131, S., Zafeiridis, I., Zenetos, A. (2023). New records of introduced species in the Mediterranean Sea (November 2023). Mediterranean Marine Science, 24(3), 610-632.\", \"Myers, P., Espinosa, R., Parr, C. S., Jones, T., Hammond, G. S., Dewey, T. A. (2025). The Animal Diversity Web (online). Accessed at: https://animaldiversity.org (25.08.2025).\", \"Rothman, B. S. S., Goren, M., Galil, B. S. (2013). Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (R\\u00fcppell, 1838) Along the Levantine Coast of the Mediterranean Sea: A Forthcoming Invasion? BioInvasions Records, 2, 85-88.\", \"Turan, C., Erg\\u00fcden, D., Uygur, N., G\\u00fcrlek, M., Erdo\\u011fan, Z. A., Sonmez, B., Uyan, A., Karan, S., Do\\u011fdu S. A. (2015). First record of the Indian Ocean twospot cardinalfish, Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Apogonidae), from Turkish marine waters. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 45(3), 319-322.\"], \"language\": \"eng\", \"license\": \"cc-by-4.0\", \"journal_title\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"journal_volume\": \"2\", \"journal_issue\": \"3\", \"journal_pages\": \"111-115\", \"imprint_publisher\": \"Tethys Environmental Science\", \"notes\": \"ISSN : 3023-7343\", \"upload_type\": \"publication\", \"publication_type\": \"article\", \"prereserve_doi\": {\"doi\": \"10.5281/zenodo.17064449\", \"recid\": 17064449}}, \"title\": \"Additional Record of Cheilodipterus novemstriatus (R\\u00fcppell, 1838) from the Aegean Sea (G\\u00f6kova Bay, T\\u00fcrkiye)\", \"links\": {\"self\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/17064449\", \"html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/17064449\", \"badge\": \"https://zenodo.org/badge/doi/.svg\", \"files\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/17064449/files\", \"bucket\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/files/0b0b3ca0-5c66-4ba4-9d57-ee224f3c4959\", \"latest_draft\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/17064449\", \"latest_draft_html\": \"https://zenodo.org/deposit/17064449\", \"publish\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/17064449/actions/publish\", \"edit\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/17064449/actions/edit\", \"discard\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/17064449/actions/discard\", \"newversion\": \"https://zenodo.org/api/deposit/depositions/17064449/actions/newversion\"}, \"record_id\": 17064449, \"owner\": 1087900, \"files\": [], \"state\": \"unsubmitted\", \"submitted\": false}'),(146,'Servet Dogdu','dogduservet@gmail.com','','',0,0,'dogduservet@gmail.com','First Visual Record of Caesio cf. teres Seale, 1906 (Perciformes: Caesionidae) in the Mediterranean Sea','',0,'An individual belonging to the Caesio genus was recorded with an underwater camera off the coast of Hatay Yayladağ on 20 May 2025 in the northeastern Mediterranean. The species, observed several times with an underwater camera in the same location, was identified as Caesio cf. teres. However, due to the lack of a physical specimen, a definitive species identification could not be made. This is the first known visual record of the Caesio cf. teres species in the Mediterranean basin. It is believed that the species recently arrived in the Mediterranean via the Lessepsian migration route through the Suez Canal.','Caesionidae, Caesio teres, Lessepsian migration, Iskenderun Bay, northeastern Mediterranean','Natural Science','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1466439-R1.pdf','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1466439-R1.docx','../paperimages/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1466439-R1.jpg','../uploadfiles/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1466439-R1.docx','../uploadfiles/COPYRIGHT_TES-1466439-R1.docx','','../reviewerCommentFile/Tethys_EnvSci _TES-1466439-R1.docx','0000-00-00','Dear authors, we are pleased to inform you that your article has been accepted for publication in its final version. We appreciate your selection of Tethys Environmental Sciences.','','','','TES-1466439-R1','TES-1466439',1,'Research Article','',0,1,0,1,1,1,0,0,'2025-09-30','2025-07-10','2025-08-23 10:22:59','2025-08-29','2025-09-05','2025-09-30','Servet Ahmet Doğdu*, Mahmut İğde, Necdet Uyğur, Cemal Turan','<br>Allen, G. R., Erdmann, M. V. (2012). Reef Fishes of the East Indies. Volumes I–III. Tropical Reef Research.\r<br>Arndt, E., Givan, O., Edelist, D., Sonin, O., Belmaker, J. (2018). Shifts in Eastern Mediterranean Fish Communities: Abundance Changes, Trait Overlap, and Possible Competition Between Native and Non-Native Species. Fishes, 3(2), 19.\r<br>Bariche, M., Fricke, R. (2018). Dipterygonotus balteatus (Valenciennes, 1830) and Caesio varilineata Carpenter, 1987, New Alien Fish in the Mediterranean Sea. BioInvasions Records, 7(2), 149-153. \r<br>Bos, A. R., Ogwang, J. (2018). First Record of Caesio varilineata (Perciformes: Caesionidae) from the Mediterranean Coast of Egypt. Marine Biodiversity Records, 11(1), 1-4.\r<br>Carpenter, K.E., (1988). FAO Species Catalogue. Vol 8. Fusilier Fishes of the World. An Annotated and Illustrated Catalogue of Caesionid Species Known to Date. FAO.\r<br>Deidun, A., Corsini-Foka, M., Marrone, A., Galdies, J., Zava, B., Crobe, V., Tinti, F. (2024). Yet Another Non-Indigenous Fish from Maltese Waters, Central Mediterranean: A First Record of Lagocephalus guentheri Miranda Ribeiro, 1915 (Tetraodontiformes, Tetraodontidae). BioInvasions Records, 13(3), 777-786. \r<br>Doğdu, S. A., Turan, C. (2024). Biological and Growth Parameters of Plotosus lineatus in the Mediterranean Sea. PeerJ, 12, e16945. \r<br>Froese, R., Pauly, D. (2025). FishBase. World Wide Web electronic publication. www.fishbase.org, version (04/2025).\r<br>Galil, B. S., Marchini, A., Occhipinti-Ambrogi, A. (2018). Mare Nostrum, Mare Quod Invaditur the History of Bioinvasions in the Mediterranean Sea. In Histories of Bioinvasions in the Mediterranean (pp. 21-49). Springer.\r<br>Golani, D. (2025). Update of Red Sea (Lessepsian) Fish Species in the Mediterranean Sea since the 2nd CIESM Atlas of Exotic Fish. Mediterranean Marine Science, 26(1), 149-155.\r<br>Khalil, M. T., Mostafa, A. B., El-Naggar, M. M. (2025). Climate Change and Lessepsian Migration to the Mediterranean Sea. In Climate Changes Impacts on Aquatic Environment: Assessment, Adaptation, Mitigation, and Road Map for Sustainable Development (pp. 85-118). Springer.\r<br>Langeneck, J., Bakiu, R., Chalari, N., Chatzigeorgiou, G., Crocetta, F., Doğdu, S.A., Durmishaj, S., Galil, B. S., García-Charton, J. A., Gülşahin, A., Hoffman, R., Leone, A., Lezzi, M., Logrieco, A., Mancini, E., Minareci, E., Petović, S., Ricci, P., Orenes-Salazar, V., Sperone, E., Spinelli, A., Stern, N., Tagar, A., Tanduo, V., Taşkın, E., Tiralongo, F., Trainito, E., Turan, C., Yapıcı, S., Zafeiridis, I., Zenetos, A. (2023). New records of introduced species in the Mediterranean Sea (November 2023). Mediterranean Marine Science, 24(3), 610-632. \r<br>Nelson, J. S. (2006). Fishes of the World (4th ed.). John Wiley and Sons.\r<br>Sliskovic, M., Bozic, K., Zanic Mikulicic, J., Kolanovic, I. (2024). Addressing the Significance of the Union List with a Focus on Marine Invasive Alien Species Impacts. Sustainability, 16(21), 9435.\r<br>Turan, C., Ergüden, D., Gürlek, M. (2016). Climate Change and Biodiversity Effects in Turkish Seas. Natural and Engineering Sciences, 1(2), 15-24.\r<br>Turan, C., Gürlek, M., Başusta, N., Uyan, A., Doğdu, S. A., Karan, S. (2018). A Checklist of the Non-Indigenous Fishes in Turkish Marine Waters. Natural and Engineering Sciences, 3(3), 333-358. \r<br>Turan, C., Ergüden, D., Gürlek, M., Doğdu, S. A. (2024). Checklist of Alien Fish Species in the Turkish Marine Ichthyofauna for Science and Policy Support. Tethys Environmental Science, 1(2), 50-86.\r<br>Zenetos, A., Doğan, A., Bakir, A. K., Chatzigeorgiou, G., Corsini-Foka, M., Dağli, E., Galanidi, M. (2024). Non-Indigenous Species (NIS) Know No Geopolitical Borders An Update of NIS in the Aegean Sea. Diversity, 17(1), 12.',2,3,'116-121',116,2025,1,109,104,0,'10.5281/zenodo.17065040','17065040','{\"created\": \"2025-09-05T18:48:43.719416+00:00\", \"modified\": \"2025-09-05T18:48:43.816358+00:00\", \"id\": 17065040, \"conceptrecid\": \"17065039\", \"metadata\": {\"title\": \"First Visual Record of Caesio cf. teres Seale, 1906 (Perciformes: Caesionidae) in the Mediterranean\", \"description\": \"On 20 May 2025, an individual belonging to the genus Caesio was recorded by underwater video at Yaylada\\u011f coast in the Mediterranean. The species observed with the underwater camera appears to be morphologically similar to Caesio teres. However, due to the lack of a physical specimen, a definitive species identification could not be made. This is the first known visual record of the Caesio teres species in the Mediterranean basin. It is believed that the species recently arrived in the Mediterranean via the Lessepsian migration route through the Suez Canal. The observation of a single individual in the region and the inability to obtain a physical fish specimen highlight the important role of video or photograph-based observations in the early detection of alien species.\", \"access_right\": \"open\", \"creators\": [{\"name\": \"Servet Ahmet Do\\u011fdu*\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Mahmut \\u0130\\u011fde\", \"affiliation\": null}, {\"name\": \"Necdet Uy\\u011fur\", \"a